Dialogue: 0,1:58:43.09,1:58:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- 干我　- 她疯了吗?\N{\rEng}- Hit me. - What, are you crazy?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:45.59,1:58:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- 回家做个良家妇女吧　- 我很清醒\N{\rEng}- Straighten up and fly right. - I'm all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:48.18,1:58:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说真的,来吧\N{\rEng}Let me make it look real. Make it look real.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.76,1:58:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- 够了　- 我没事,来吧\N{\rEng}- Knock it off. - I'm all right. Let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:54.06,1:58:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 别闹了　- 快点强奸我\N{\rEng}- Come on, cut the act. - Hit me!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:56.68,1:59:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,这是她自己要求的,上吧,堵住她的嘴\N{\rEng}She said hit her. Go ahead, rap her in the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:00.73,1:59:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 强奸我　- 我这就来,你个贱女人\N{\rEng}- Hit me! - I'll hit you! You bitch!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:06.36,1:59:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你个畜生　- 快点插进去吧\N{\rEng}- You animal! - Put a cork in her.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:13.87,1:59:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:15.16,1:59:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不要\N{\rEng}No. Don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:17.41,1:59:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,不要啊\N{\rEng}Don't. No!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:20.25,1:59:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,不,你这个肮脏的混球\N{\rEng}No! You dirty bastards!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:30.51,1:59:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,混球!\N{\rEng}Bastards!
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.18,1:59:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,打开隐藏的抽屉\N{\rEng}Try the secret compartment.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:47.44,1:59:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这就对了\N{\rEng}Attaboy.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:58.95,2:00:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,多谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:24.35,2:00:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,好棒的逾越节薄饼汤圆\N{\rEng}Nice matzo balls.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:32.86,2:00:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧,多漂亮啊\N{\rEng}Beautiful. Look at that.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:37.16,2:00:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,好了,包起来吧\N{\rEng}Okay, better wrap them up.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:48.59,2:00:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要走了,你呢?\N{\rEng}We're going. You coming?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:53.80,2:00:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,这就来\N{\rEng}Coming.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:42.73,2:01:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 早上好　- 钻石到手了吗?\N{\rEng}- Morning. - You get the stones?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.29,2:02:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,拿钱给他\N{\rEng}Pay him.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:33.82,2:02:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有什么问题吗?　- 没有,小事一桩\N{\rEng}- Any trouble? - No trouble. Kid stuff.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:32.96,2:05:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么没告诉我?　- 牢狱生活改变了你\N{\rEng}- How come you didn't tell me? - Being inside can change you.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:37.04,2:05:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经答应弗兰克除掉乔\N{\rEng}I'd already made the deal with Frankie to get rid of Joe.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:40.09,2:05:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,和法兰克麦诺迪做生意,你不能出尔反尔\N{\rEng}With the man like Frankie Monaldi you don't say, "yes" and then say, "no."
Dialogue: 0,2:05:44.34,2:05:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,你说得对,我早该拒绝的\N{\rEng}You're right. I would have said, no.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:46.68,2:05:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,弗兰克是个狠角色\N{\rEng}Frankie Monaldi is as big as they come.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:48.85,2:05:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,他手下弟兄众多\N{\rEng}He's got the combination in the palm of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:51.06,2:05:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我们稍不小心,就会栽在他的手上\N{\rEng}If we're not careful, he's gonna have us in the palm of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:54.06,2:05:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,孤军奋斗是没有前途的\N{\rEng}You don't get nowhere alone.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:56.85,2:05:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你不喜欢替别人做事\N{\rEng}I thought you were the guy who said you didn't like bosses.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:59.36,2:06:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,那时候这样是个明智之举,现在也是一样\N{\rEng}It sounded like a good idea then. It still is.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.69,2:06:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,好好想一想吧,面条\N{\rEng}Let's just think about it, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:04.03,2:06:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,他们会要求我们加入,然后我们会受益颇多\N{\rEng}They're gonna ask us to come in with them. There's a lot in it for us.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:10.99,2:06:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,今天他们让我们除掉乔\N{\rEng}Today they asked us to get rid of Joe.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:12.83,2:06:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,明天他们就会让我除掉你\N{\rEng}Tomorrow they ask me to get rid of you.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:15.66,2:06:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你答应吗?我可是不会答应\N{\rEng}Is that okay with you? 'Cause it's not okay with me.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:22.05,2:06:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}All right.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:25.05,2:06:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,这件事到此为止吧\N{\rEng}Let's just forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:40.48,2:06:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,想游泳吗?\N{\rEng}Wanna go for a swim?
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.40,2:06:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,好,咱们去游泳\N{\rEng}Yeah, let's go for a swim.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:57.96,2:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你在做什么?\N{\rEng}All right, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:00.13,2:07:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,面条,别做蠢事\N{\rEng}Hey, Noodles. Don't fuck around, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:06.63,2:07:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 面条你在做什么?　- 嘿!\N{\rEng}- Noodles, what are you doing? - Hey!
Dialogue: 0,2:07:09.22,2:07:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了吗?\N{\rEng}You crazy?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:14.26,2:07:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,操\N{\rEng}Shit.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:22.77,2:07:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,妈的!没想到你会做出这种事\N{\rEng}Asshole! Can't believe you did this!
Dialogue: 0,2:10:50.44,2:10:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"地方检察官詹姆斯李斯特在一起汽车爆炸中不幸罹难\N{\rEng}"District Attorney James Lister was killed in an explosion of a car
Dialogue: 0,2:10:53.73,2:10:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"当时他正乘坐商务部秘书长贝利的汽车\N{\rEng}belonging to Secretary of Commerce Christopher Bailey
Dialogue: 0,2:10:56.82,2:11:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"从秘书长位于长岛的府邸离开\N{\rEng}as he was leaving the secretary's Long Island estate.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:00.45,2:11:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"当场身亡的李斯特先生,原定将于周四前往华盛顿\N{\rEng}Mr. Lister, who was killed instantly in the blast, was scheduled to testify
Dialogue: 0,2:11:04.04,2:11:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"出席参议院的一场听证会\N{\rEng}in Washington on Thursday before a Senate committee.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:07.37,2:11:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"此委员会负责调查的正是"贝利丑闻"\N{\rEng}A committee investigating what has come to be called "The Bailey Scandal."
Dialogue: 0,2:11:11.54,2:11:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"此案件已经交由专案组调查\N{\rEng}A special team of detectives has been assigned to the case.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:15.09,2:11:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,"秘书长贝利尚未对此事发表任何评论"\N{\rEng}As for Secretary Bailey, he was not available for any statement at this time."
Dialogue: 0,2:11:20.80,2:11:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识他们?\N{\rEng}Did you know those guys?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:22.10,2:11:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"…他的法律顾问,欧文高德\N{\rEng}"...offices of his long-time legal advisor, Irving Gold...
Dialogue: 0,2:11:25.60,2:11:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"希望他能透露些许讯息\N{\rEng}...in hopes of getting some comment.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:28.31,2:11:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"高德先生,你知道地方检察官李斯特\N{\rEng}Mr. Gold, you're aware that District Attorney Lister
Dialogue: 0,2:11:33.52,2:11:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,"是贝利丑闻案中第二位突然死亡的证人\N{\rEng}is the second witness in the Bailey Scandal to meet a sudden and violent end.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:36.99,2:11:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"第一位是副秘书长托马斯芬尼\N{\rEng}The first was Thomas Finney, undersecretary of commerce
Dialogue: 0,2:11:40.66,2:11:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"一个月前,他自十五楼的办公室坠楼而亡\N{\rEng}who fell to his death from his 15th-floor office just a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:11:45.04,2:11:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"这其中是否有所联系…?"\N{\rEng}You think there's a connection between...?"
Dialogue: 0,2:11:46.54,2:11:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,快拿着钱离开,面条,还待在这里干嘛?\N{\rEng}Take the money and run, Noodles. What the hell's keeping you here?
Dialogue: 0,2:11:51.79,2:11:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"目前唯一的证人\N{\rEng}"The only remaining witness is the man who
Dialogue: 0,2:11:54.80,2:11:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,"正是本案的主角\N{\rEng}rightly or wrongly has given his name to this whole affair,
Dialogue: 0,2:11:57.92,2:11:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"秘书长贝利"\N{\rEng}Secretary Christopher Bailey."
Dialogue: 0,2:12:00.09,2:12:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,真诡异\N{\rEng}Curious.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:03.01,2:12:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"- 秘书长毫不担心　- 既然他毫不担心\N{\rEng}"- The secretary has no worries. - Sir, if he has no worries,
Dialogue: 0,2:12:06.39,2:12:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,"那他为何会躲到位于长岛的住宅?\N{\rEng}why then has he retreated to his place on Long Island?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:10.19,2:12:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"他正在考虑如何对委员会提出的问题\N{\rEng}Far from retreating, he's preparing his attack on the questions
Dialogue: 0,2:12:13.94,2:12:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"做出回击\N{\rEng}he will be asked by the committee.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:16.11,2:12:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"我想说'指控'比'问题'更为贴切吧\N{\rEng}I'd call them accusations more than questions, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:18.82,2:12:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"- 他并无顾虑　- 公众们有\N{\rEng}- The secretary has no worries. - Well, the public does.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:21.66,2:12:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"尤其是对于那些流言,非法合约\N{\rEng}Particularly, in view of the rumors about rigged contracts,
Dialogue: 0,2:12:24.95,2:12:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"贿赂还有国际黑手党\N{\rEng}bribery, the international Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:27.83,2:12:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"特别是非法挪用运输工会的退休基金\N{\rEng}Especially those dealing with the illegal use of the Transport union pension funds.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:34.04,2:12:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"请问你对此作何评论?\N{\rEng}Could you tell us anything about that?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:36.55,2:12:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"各位,我否认所有,针对本组织的流言与指控\N{\rEng}Gentlemen, I deny all of these rumors and allegations directed against my organization.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:42.55,2:12:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,"我们一向奉公守法,并将一如既往洁身自爱\N{\rEng}Our hands have always been and will continue to remain clean.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:47.18,2:12:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"我毕生都致力于保证美国劳工运动的干净透明"\N{\rEng}In my entire life, I've fought to keep the American labor movement clear..."
Dialogue: 0,2:12:52.90,2:12:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯,我认识他\N{\rEng}Him, I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:54.10,2:12:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"…投机买卖,犯罪行为\N{\rEng}"...forced speculation, criminal elements
Dialogue: 0,2:12:57.32,2:13:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"或腐败的政客,如有任何错误…"\N{\rEng}or corrupt politicians. If any mistakes have been made..."
Dialogue: 0,2:13:02.07,2:13:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他还是老样子,满口的屁话\N{\rEng}He's still giving out the same old bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:05.37,2:13:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"任何犯罪行为,都与我们无关"\N{\rEng}"If any guilt at all exists in this situation, it lies elsewhere."
Dialogue: 0,2:13:50.87,2:13:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我怎么总能在报纸上看到关于你的新闻?\N{\rEng}What's this I've been reading about you in the newspapers?
Dialogue: 0,2:13:57.50,2:14:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,工会领袖发出怒吼?\N{\rEng}Inflammatory words from a union boss?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:06.43,2:14:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你阻止不了工人阶级和社会运动的\N{\rEng}You still won't come and stop the workers or the social movement.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:12.22,2:14:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,给我听好了,你这个社会主义的混蛋\N{\rEng}Listen to me, you socialist asshole!
Dialogue: 0,2:14:15.64,2:14:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不喜欢社会主义倾向的劳工还有他们发起的运动\N{\rEng}We don't give a good fart about the socialist workers and their movements.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:21.15,2:14:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你们最好立刻滚出工厂,不要妨碍我们重新开工\N{\rEng}We just want you out of the factory so we can get the furnaces working again.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:26.32,2:14:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们最后一次开出条件\N{\rEng}This is the last offer you're gonna get.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:29.49,2:14:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你是签还是不签?\N{\rEng}You want to sign it or what?
Dialogue: 0,2:14:38.42,2:14:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,跟你的老板说,让他留着擦屁股去吧\N{\rEng}Tell your bosses they can wipe their ass with it.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:48.09,2:14:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,倒满\N{\rEng}Fill her up.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:14.75,2:15:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我最后再问你…\N{\rEng}This is my last...
Dialogue: 0,2:15:23.42,2:15:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,住手,别开枪\N{\rEng}Hold it, boys. Don't shoot.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:27.76,2:15:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,是我,康宁\N{\rEng}It's me, Crowning.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:42.98,2:15:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- 康宁　- 是我\N{\rEng}- Crowning. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:45.90,2:15:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,到此为止吧\N{\rEng}That'll do, boys.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:47.74,2:15:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么?\N{\rEng}What'll do?
Dialogue: 0,2:15:49.74,2:15:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这家伙差点就要屈服了\N{\rEng}We almost got the kid where we want him.
Dialogue: 0,2:15:56.87,2:15:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你的老板也已经妥协了\N{\rEng}And we got the boss where we want him.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:00.12,2:16:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,别乱来\N{\rEng}Easy.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:02.75,2:16:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,别乱来\N{\rEng}Easy.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:08.09,2:16:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,把枪放下\N{\rEng}Put 'em down.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:11.18,2:16:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,把枪放下吧\N{\rEng}Put your guns away, boys.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:23.56,2:16:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只想交换人质\N{\rEng}Just swapping prisoners.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:26.27,2:16:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这交易很公平吧,猪头?\N{\rEng}Fair trade, huh, chickenhead?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:36.28,2:16:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,工会成员交换你们的老板\N{\rEng}Union boy over here for Mr. Boss Man.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:39.62,2:16:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,瞧,是什么人来了\N{\rEng}Well, look who's here.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:42.92,2:16:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,肥摩坟场的小朋友们\N{\rEng}Fat Moe's boneyard boys.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:45.84,2:16:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这倒让我想起来了\N{\rEng}Which reminds me.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:48.34,2:16:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你的癌症怎么样了,乔?\N{\rEng}How's that cancer in your gut coming along, Chicken Joe?
Dialogue: 0,2:16:54.18,2:16:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 给他松绑　- 你无权命令我\N{\rEng}- Untie him. - I don't take orders from you.
Dialogue: 0,2:16:58.22,2:17:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不是在叫你听我们的命令,我们是在告诉你\N{\rEng}We're not asking you to take orders, Joe. We're telling you.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:01.56,2:17:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,现在去给他松绑\N{\rEng}Now go ahead, untie him.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:03.90,2:17:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,给他松绑吧\N{\rEng}Untie him.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:43.19,2:17:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你们是什么人?\N{\rEng}Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:46.19,2:17:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你们替谁工作?\N{\rEng}Who's paying you?
Dialogue: 0,2:17:48.23,2:17:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我想你听了后一定会火冒三丈的,麦克\N{\rEng}I think this is really gonna piss you off, Mac.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:51.49,2:17:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,是你的那些肮脏的政客朋友们\N{\rEng}I think it's those dirty politician friends of yours.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:55.20,2:17:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,是吗?滚回去告诉他们我不需要你们插手\N{\rEng}Yeah? Well, you crawl back and tell 'em we don't want you in with us.
Dialogue: 0,2:17:59.99,2:18:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我不想我们的抗争活动和私酒娼妓毒品扯上关系\N{\rEng}Our fight's got nothing to do with liquor and prostitution and dope.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:04.08,2:18:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你最好尽快习惯这事儿吧,老兄\N{\rEng}Well, you'd better get used to the idea, pal.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:07.33,2:18:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,国家仍在不断的成长之中\N{\rEng}This country is still growing up.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:09.55,2:18:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,有些病,晚来不如早来\N{\rEng}Certain diseases it's better to have when you're still young.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:15.26,2:18:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,你们可不是麻疹,你们是瘟疫\N{\rEng}You boys ain't a mild case of the measles. You're the plague.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:20.22,2:18:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,而像他那种混蛋,早就已经免疫了\N{\rEng}Bastards like him are immune.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:22.43,2:18:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们和他们之间的区别\N{\rEng}That's the difference between us and them!
Dialogue: 0,2:18:27.56,2:18:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,别激动\N{\rEng}Take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:29.57,2:18:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,区别在于,他们永远是赢家\N{\rEng}The difference is, they're always gonna win.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:31.73,2:18:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,而你们永远是输家\N{\rEng}And you're gonna keep getting it up the ass.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:34.49,2:18:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,(输得)比你想得还快\N{\rEng}Sooner than you think.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:53.76,2:18:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,艾耶罗警长,将警察调入工厂\N{\rEng}Chief Aiello, moving policemen into the factory came as a surprise to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:58.14,2:19:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,对媒体,工会,特别是示威者,是个极大的震撼\N{\rEng}The press, the unions, especially the strikers.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:01.01,2:19:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,要不然呢,甜心?宣战不成?\N{\rEng}Well, what did you want, sweetheart? A declaration of war?
Dialogue: 0,2:19:03.77,2:19:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的行动很温和\N{\rEng}Ours was a peaceable operation.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:05.68,2:19:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,此举不与新的工会法相抵触吗?\N{\rEng}Wasn't that contrary to new union laws?
Dialogue: 0,2:19:08.23,2:19:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我领导的是警察,不是人民\N{\rEng}I'm chief of police, not chief of people.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:10.61,2:19:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,抗议者是否有暴力行为,以便合理化…\N{\rEng}Was there any violence to justify...
Dialogue: 0,2:19:13.11,2:19:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,我的信条是：预防胜于镇压\N{\rEng}My motto is: "Prevention, not repression."
Dialogue: 0,2:19:16.95,2:19:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你让工贼进去工作\N{\rEng}But you let scabs move in and start working.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:19.20,2:19:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,年轻的女士,如果你是在跟我说话的话,那么请称他们为"失业的劳工"\N{\rEng}Young lady, you wanna talk to me, call them "unemployed workers."
Dialogue: 0,2:19:23.24,2:19:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不介意的话\N{\rEng}With your permission,
Dialogue: 0,2:19:24.83,2:19:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,我得赶在这些花枯萎前,送给我的妻子\N{\rEng}I'll take these flowers to my missis before they wilt.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:28.96,2:19:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你们应该也有所耳闻,我有儿子了!\N{\rEng}Or maybe you heard. I'm the father of a baby boy.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:35.13,2:19:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,警长,最后一个问题\N{\rEng}Chief, one more question.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:37.80,2:19:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我们听说你刚出生的儿子\N{\rEng}We heard he's the youngest stockholder
Dialogue: 0,2:19:39.80,2:19:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,是那家工厂最年轻的股东\N{\rEng}in that factory you occupied.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:46.98,2:19:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你这话什么意思?\N{\rEng}What'd you mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,2:19:49.10,2:19:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说这是工厂主管们送给那孩子的礼物,以表谢意\N{\rEng}They say management expressed their thanks with a birthday present for the baby.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:56.69,2:19:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?诽谤可是个重罪\N{\rEng}You know, slander is a serious offense.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:59.49,2:20:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,特别出自记者的口中\N{\rEng}Especially when it comes from a hack reporter.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:02.24,2:20:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,想知道这会被判多重的刑吗?\N{\rEng}You wanna find out how serious?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:07.12,2:20:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,不过既然他是我连生四个女儿后的第一个儿子\N{\rEng}But since this is my first boy after four girls...
Dialogue: 0,2:20:12.29,2:20:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我大人不计小人过\N{\rEng}...I'll declare amnesty.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:16.51,2:20:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,放你一码\N{\rEng}Behave yourself.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:20.22,2:20:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,开车\N{\rEng}Go.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:33.35,2:22:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢你\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:36.52,2:22:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,他吃过奶了吗?\N{\rEng}- He's eating? - Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:38.27,2:22:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 喝了五次了　- 五次?那又有何妨\N{\rEng}- For five. - For five? Well, why not.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:41.86,2:22:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你的奶水那么多,够喂养一只军队的\N{\rEng}You could feed an army with these two milk plants.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:44.82,2:22:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以开个乳品店了\N{\rEng}We could open up a dairy.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:49.53,2:22:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿,姑娘们\N{\rEng}Oh, hey. Che bella.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:52.87,2:22:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,谁爱你们?我爱你\N{\rEng}Who loves you? Who loves you? I love you.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:58.83,2:23:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我也爱你\N{\rEng}And I love you. And I love you.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:02.84,2:23:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,露西\N{\rEng}Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,2:23:04.63,2:23:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,六点了,他是不是该喝奶了?\N{\rEng}- Don't you have to feed him at 6:00? - Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:08.05,2:23:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,请进\N{\rEng}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:11.18,2:23:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,- 哦,他来了　- 我儿子\N{\rEng}- Oh, here he is now. - That's my son.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:14.93,2:23:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我儿子\N{\rEng}That's my son.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:21.06,2:23:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我儿子,这是我儿子\N{\rEng}That's my son! That's my son!
Dialogue: 0,2:23:26.86,2:23:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,天啊,小宝宝变得可真快\N{\rEng}Jesus Christ, they change fast.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:30.16,2:23:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,不过他长得还真像他爷爷\N{\rEng}Yeah, but he looks like my old man.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:32.99,2:23:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,是啊,看看,一模一样的眼睛\N{\rEng}Yeah, yeah, look, same eyes.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:35.04,2:23:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,一样的傲气\N{\rEng}And look, the same devilish pride.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:37.58,2:23:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿,嘿,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey. Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:40.63,2:23:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你看过他的小鸡鸡了吗?\N{\rEng}Did you see his dickey?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:42.34,2:23:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- 文森特　- 咋了?\N{\rEng}- Vincent. - What?
Dialogue: 0,2:23:44.46,2:23:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- 女儿们在这儿呢　- 女儿们\N{\rEng}- The girls. - The girls!
Dialogue: 0,2:23:46.88,2:23:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,早晚你们得知道,在我之后\N{\rEng}Sooner or later you have to learn that after me,
Dialogue: 0,2:23:49.51,2:23:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他就是你们的一家之主\N{\rEng}the boss in the house is him.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:52.97,2:23:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他跟他老爹一样,是有鸡鸡的人\N{\rEng}He's got balls like his papa.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:54.93,2:23:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- 嘿　- 让我来\N{\rEng}- Hey! - Let me have him.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:56.35,2:24:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不,不,不,我要亲自来\N{\rEng}No, no, no. I'll do this. I'll do this, huh.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:01.81,2:24:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:05.36,2:24:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,看呐\N{\rEng}Look. Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:12.03,2:24:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,爸爸帮你来换尿布\N{\rEng}Let Papa change you.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:13.53,2:24:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,没事的,没事的\N{\rEng}Come on, everything will be swell.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:15.91,2:24:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,放松,放松\N{\rEng}Come on, come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:22.00,2:24:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这他妈的怎么回事\N{\rEng}What the fuck is this?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:24.17,2:24:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- 这怎么回事?　- 噢,不!\N{\rEng}- What is this? Huh? What's that? - Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,2:24:30.26,2:24:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,号码没错啊\N{\rEng}- Look! - It's the right number.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:32.68,2:24:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,号码没有错?看我不扭断你的脖子\N{\rEng}The right number? I'll break your goddamn neck!
Dialogue: 0,2:24:36.18,2:24:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,找回我的儿子,不然一把火把你这儿全烧了\N{\rEng}Find my son, or I'll burn down this whole goddamn building.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:41.48,2:24:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你好,给我闭嘴\N{\rEng}Hello. Would you shut up?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:44.11,2:24:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,噢,不,等等,我不是在说你\N{\rEng}No, hey, no. Wait, wait. I'm not talking to you.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:48.61,2:24:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你是…?\N{\rEng}Well, who's this?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:50.99,2:24:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,无所谓了,你到底是谁?\N{\rEng}Never mind. To whom am I talking?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:53.57,2:24:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你他妈的到底是谁?我儿子呢?他在哪儿?\N{\rEng}Who the hell are you? My son, where is he?
Dialogue: 0,2:24:56.54,2:25:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为呢?他当然在育婴室咯,半步也未曾离开过\N{\rEng}Where the hell do you think he is? He's in the maternity ward. He never left.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:00.75,2:25:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,他有些烦躁,所以想换个床\N{\rEng}He just got a little restless, so he wanted to change his bed. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:04.25,2:25:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,其他的宝宝也有此意,所以他们就换了个位置,就是这样\N{\rEng}And the other kids got the same idea, so they also wanted to change their beds.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:08.13,2:25:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,于是,三,四十个婴儿蹦蹦跳跳就把床位给换了\N{\rEng}You got 30, 40 screaming babies jumping from one bed to another switching tags,
Dialogue: 0,2:25:12.93,2:25:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,这下我们有麻烦了\N{\rEng}so now we do have a real problem.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:15.68,2:25:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,人渣,操他妈的赶紧把儿子还给我\N{\rEng}Piece of shit whoever you are! What the fuck! I want my son!
Dialogue: 0,2:25:20.31,2:25:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,幸运的是,我们当时也在场,所以一切尽在我们的掌控之中\N{\rEng}Luckily, we were there to see that everything was under control.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:24.73,2:25:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你愿意的话,我可以让他们回到原位\N{\rEng}If you want, we can put everything back where it was.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:27.23,2:25:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- 只是有一个问题,你得跟我们合作　- 说吧!\N{\rEng}- Except this one problem, you gotta meet us halfway. - Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,2:25:31.45,2:25:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么会如此关心这场罢工的输赢?\N{\rEng}Why do you give a fuck about who wins this strike?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:33.91,2:25:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,此事与我无关,我什么都没做\N{\rEng}That's got nothing to do with me! What did I do?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:36.53,2:25:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你什么都没做?首先,你让工贼进入\N{\rEng}What did you do? First of all, you let the scabs in.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:39.08,2:25:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,接着,你派警察去保护他们\N{\rEng}Second of all, you've got the cops in there protecting them. That's what you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:42.42,2:25:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我是个警察　- 好了,给我闭嘴,我来告诉你怎么做\N{\rEng}- I'm a cop! - All right, shut the fuck up, and I'm gonna tell you what you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:45.29,2:25:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,给我听仔细了\N{\rEng}Now listen to me very carefully.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:47.46,2:25:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,撤走你的走狗们,让罢工的劳工和他们的老板自行解决问题\N{\rEng}You're gonna call off your dogs and you're gonna let the strikers work it out with the bosses. You got that?
Dialogue: 0,2:25:51.21,2:25:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,把我儿子现在就还给我!\N{\rEng}I want my son back now!
Dialogue: 0,2:25:52.84,2:25:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,照我说的做,我就把你儿子的号码告诉你\N{\rEng}You do that and we'll give you the kid's number.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:55.09,2:25:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,否则的话,自己去找你儿子吧,祝你好运\N{\rEng}You don't do that, look for your kid yourself. And good luck.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:59.10,2:26:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- 想清楚了吗?　- 好吧\N{\rEng}- So, what is it gonna be? - Okay.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:01.52,2:26:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我这就把我的人撤回　- 好孩子\N{\rEng}- I'll call my men off today. - Attaboy.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:04.60,2:26:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗,就一个败类而言\N{\rEng}You know, for a rotten bastard son of a bitch
Dialogue: 0,2:26:07.94,2:26:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有我想象得那么笨\N{\rEng}you're not as stupid as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:11.53,2:26:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好了,我们会再联系你的　- 什么时候?\N{\rEng}- Alright, we'll be in touch with you. - When do you gonna call?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:14.24,2:26:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心,别担心,我们会再联系你的\N{\rEng}Don't worry, don't worry. We'll be in touch with you.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:17.49,2:26:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- 再见　- 我还…\N{\rEng}- Bye. - I got to...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:22.58,2:26:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- 如何?　- 搞定\N{\rEng}- So? - We got a deal.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:29.29,2:26:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他还挺好商量的嘛　- 是啊\N{\rEng}- To a very smooth talker. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:31.71,2:26:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,干杯\N{\rEng}- Mazel. - At least.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:34.68,2:26:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,佩格勒\N{\rEng}Peggeleh.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:42.18,2:26:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,换婴儿的名单呢?\N{\rEng}Where's that switch list?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:44.39,2:26:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 名单?　- 对\N{\rEng}- The switch list? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:48.15,2:26:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- 找不到了　- 什么?\N{\rEng}- I can't find it. - What?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:50.02,2:26:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我找不到了\N{\rEng}I can't find it.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:53.07,2:26:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你把它弄哪儿去了?　- 我想我把它跟外套一起弄丢了\N{\rEng}- What'd you do with it? - I think I dumped it with that hopital jacket.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:56.28,2:26:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,真是个笨蛋\N{\rEng}What a yutz.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:58.03,2:27:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,等等,听我说\N{\rEng}- Oh, Pat. - Wait a minute, listen.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:00.37,2:27:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,听我说,面条,我想起来了\N{\rEng}Listen, Noodles, Noodles, wait. I remember.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:03.37,2:27:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,男婴的号码是奇数,不,偶数,女婴是奇数\N{\rEng}The boys' numbers was odd... Was even, and the girls' was odd.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:07.46,2:27:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- 很简单嘛　- 你表现得不错\N{\rEng}- That's very simple. - You took good stock.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:09.75,2:27:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,那我们就帮他选个偶数吧\N{\rEng}Hey, you know what? Let's give him an even number.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:12.21,2:27:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,八,咱们就选八吧\N{\rEng}Eight. Let's pick an eight.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:14.76,2:27:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,八\N{\rEng}Eight.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:18.76,2:27:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- 好,这是个好数字　- 等等,那其他的小宝宝呢?\N{\rEng}- Yeah, it's a good number. -Wait a minute. What about the other little pischers?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:24.31,2:27:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是命运的主宰\N{\rEng}We're better than fate.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:26.69,2:27:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我们让某些人过好日子,某些人过苦日子\N{\rEng}We give some the good life, give it to others right up the ass.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:32.61,2:27:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,好啦,各位,今天是周六,该分钱了\N{\rEng}All right, boys, let's settle up. It's Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:36.24,2:27:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,分个屁,我要去狂欢\N{\rEng}Settle-shmettle, I'm gonna take mine out in trade.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:39.78,2:27:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是讨厌\N{\rEng}You're such a nudge.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:42.74,2:27:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?我希望我小时候也被掉包了\N{\rEng}You know what? I wish I was switched when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:47.08,2:27:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你怎么知道你没有呢?\N{\rEng}What makes you think you weren't?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:04.64,2:28:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我可不敢相信\N{\rEng}I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:07.64,2:28:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿,你们快过来,看看那边的是谁?\N{\rEng}Hey, you guys, come here. Take a look at who's over here.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:11.69,2:28:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那样可以吗,佩姬?　- 可以\N{\rEng}- That suit you, Peg? - Yeah. Okay. Fine, Max.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:14.15,2:28:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你发现什么了?　- 那边,那边\N{\rEng}- What've you got? - Over there.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:19.15,2:28:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\rEng}Well, what...
Dialogue: 0,2:28:26.33,2:28:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我他妈的!面条,面条,快过来\N{\rEng}Holy shit! Noodles! Noodles! Come here, come here.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:30.67,2:28:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,看\N{\rEng}Look.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:34.34,2:28:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,钢琴旁的金发妞\N{\rEng}The blond by the piano.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:40.43,2:28:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那是谁?　- 那是谁?\N{\rEng}- Who's that? - Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,2:28:42.51,2:28:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你曾和这女人连为一体\N{\rEng}You and this broad were practically engaged at one point.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:46.97,2:28:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,哦,干我,哦,我好喜欢这样\N{\rEng}Oh, beat me. Oh, I love it.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:51.31,2:28:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- 到底是谁?底特律的那个骚货?　- 没错\N{\rEng}- Who was it? The Detroit cock-squasher? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:53.98,2:28:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 佩姬　- 不,长得不太像\N{\rEng}- Peggy. - No, she looks different.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:56.53,2:28:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识桌子边上的那个穿花裙子的金发妞吗?\N{\rEng}You know that platinum blond over there with a flower dress? Now She's by the table.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:00.03,2:29:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,看到了吗?能把她叫进来吗?\N{\rEng}See her? Call her in, will you?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:09.08,2:29:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- 卡萝　- 卡萝?无所谓了\N{\rEng}- Carol. - Carol, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:10.71,2:29:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就说这里有些她的老朋友\N{\rEng}Just tell her there's a bunch of her old friends here. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:16.42,2:29:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,卡萝\N{\rEng}Carol.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:18.17,2:29:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,卡萝\N{\rEng}Carol!
Dialogue: 0,2:29:25.05,2:29:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,面条,过来\N{\rEng}Noodles, come here.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:30.64,2:29:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有人想见你　- 谁?\N{\rEng}- Somebody here wants to see you. - Who?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:34.90,2:29:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识他们吗?\N{\rEng}You know these guys?
Dialogue: 0,2:29:38.94,2:29:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,不认识\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:42.24,2:29:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我认识吗?\N{\rEng}I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:48.54,2:29:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:50.20,2:29:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,不,这样的一群帅哥,我应该记得\N{\rEng}No. I'd remember a bunch of good-lookers like these.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:11.52,2:30:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,噢,好吧,我怎么会忘呢\N{\rEng}Oh, well, how could I forget.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:21.44,2:30:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,有一个…\N{\rEng}There was...
Dialogue: 0,2:30:23.99,2:30:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不过我只对你们其中的一个,有深刻的印象\N{\rEng}There was only one of you I got to know personally, though.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:31.37,2:30:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,哪一个?\N{\rEng}Which one?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:33.25,2:30:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们来试试你认人的功力吧\N{\rEng}Let's see how good a memory you've got for faces.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:56.81,2:30:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,你\N{\rEng}You.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:59.40,2:31:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:01.57,2:31:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他\N{\rEng}Him.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:02.99,2:31:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在一起的时间太久,长相都变得相似了\N{\rEng}We've been hanging out so long together we're starting to look alike.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:18.96,2:31:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,销魂\N{\rEng}Charmed.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:38.81,2:31:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以叫我卡萝\N{\rEng}You can call me Carol.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:52.33,2:31:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经见过面了\N{\rEng}We've already met.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:12.81,2:32:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,幸会\N{\rEng}Pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:15.93,2:32:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,这是\N{\rEng}The pleasure...
Dialogue: 0,2:32:18.23,2:32:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我的荣幸\N{\rEng}...is all mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:47.47,2:32:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,这么看来,你离开了底特律?\N{\rEng}So you left Detroit, huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:32:50.51,2:32:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不,她只是和她老公来这里度周末\N{\rEng}No. Her and her husband just come in on the weekends.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:53.43,2:32:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,这里可比海边刺激\N{\rEng}Yeah, beats the seashore.
Dialogue: 0,2:32:56.39,2:33:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他一次对付十个男人,而他的老公则在一旁窥视\N{\rEng}Well, she takes on maybe 10 guys while her hubby watches through the peephole.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:00.64,2:33:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,可比看电影还过瘾\N{\rEng}Beats the hell out of the movies.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:02.94,2:33:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,不知道那龟孙子是否还在房里?\N{\rEng}I wonder what that poor jerk is up to in his cubbyhole right now?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:05.73,2:33:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,他一定在想,他的风骚老婆去哪里了\N{\rEng}He must be wondering where is his fucking wife.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:16.08,2:33:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,要不咱们来3P吧?\N{\rEng}Why don't we make it a threesome, huh?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:20.04,2:33:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,你看不出他今晚另有去处?\N{\rEng}Can't you see he's got other plans for tonight?
Dialogue: 0,2:33:23.33,2:33:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,把她也带来,咱们来群P\N{\rEng}Well, bring her along. We'll make it a foursome.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:31.72,2:33:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我不是那种人\N{\rEng}I'm not that kind of guy.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:35.05,2:33:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我怕你会爱我爱得无法自拔\N{\rEng}Besides, I'm afraid if I give you a good crack in the mouth, you'd probably like it.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:53.28,2:33:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,晚安了,各位\N{\rEng}Have a good night, fellas.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:56.37,2:33:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,一会儿见\N{\rEng}See you later.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:05.60,2:34:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他们要你穿得好像那些正要烧光犹太人商店\N{\rEng}They make you dress like those lunatics who go around Germany
Dialogue: 0,2:34:08.16,2:34:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,疯狂的德国党卫队\N{\rEng}burning down all those Jewish stores.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:10.84,2:34:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,那些疯子也烧了我们的店铺,逼迫我们来到美国\N{\rEng}Those lunatics burned down also our store and made us go to America.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:16.47,2:34:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我也是犹太人　- 我知道,先生\N{\rEng}- I'm Jewish too. - I know, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:19.35,2:34:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 每个人都知道　- 知道什么?\N{\rEng}- Everybody knows. - Knows what?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:24.39,2:34:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,每个人都知道你是谁\N{\rEng}Everybody knows who you are, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:30.82,2:34:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 那你以为呢?　- 我没有看法,这与我无关,先生\N{\rEng}- And what do you think? -I don't think, it's your business, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:35.20,2:34:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,不,你有看法\N{\rEng}No, you think.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:38.33,2:34:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你是不是觉得这是个耻辱?\N{\rEng}You think it's a disgrace, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:41.33,2:34:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不必像那些意大利人一样\N{\rEng}We Jews, sir, don't have to be like the Italians,
Dialogue: 0,2:34:43.87,2:34:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,敬仰违法者\N{\rEng}who look up to the lawbreakers.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:46.79,2:34:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然我们不是黑帮,但我们依然有很多敌人,先生\N{\rEng}We have enough enemies without becoming gangsters, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:51.17,2:34:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,你一周能赚多少钱?\N{\rEng}How much money do you make a week?
Dialogue: 0,2:34:54.01,2:34:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,不是每个人都像你一样出手大方,先生\N{\rEng}Not everybody tips like you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:56.30,2:34:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我赚的钱足以应付我去学校念书\N{\rEng}I make enough to go to school and learn for my degree.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:59.39,2:35:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这是为了你好,或许到你六十岁的时候,你才能赚够钱\N{\rEng}Good for you. So maybe by the time you are 60, you'll make enough,
Dialogue: 0,2:35:02.81,2:35:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,但你也就只能有这些钱,没法赚到更多了\N{\rEng}but then you won't be able to get it up anymore.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:20.99,2:35:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 等很久了吧?　- 等了一辈子了\N{\rEng}- Been waiting long? - All my life.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:44.39,2:35:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你说你想要一个海边的餐厅,所以我就选了这里\N{\rEng}You said you wanted a place by the ocean. So I had it opened.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:47.23,2:35:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,这个季节,这里原本是不营业的,但我让他们又开张了\N{\rEng}It was closed for the season.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:49.06,2:35:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,这儿所有的桌子都只供我们两个人用\N{\rEng}All these tables are for two people.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:52.19,2:35:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,随便哪张桌子都行\N{\rEng}Pick whatever one you want.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:26.18,2:36:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我想就这里吧\N{\rEng}I like this one.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:27.98,2:36:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,来,坐吧\N{\rEng}Here, sit down.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:36.86,2:36:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,红酒炖牛肉,白酒炖小牛肉\N{\rEng}Boeuf à la mode. Blanquette de veau.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:39.57,2:36:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我要油醋白芦笋和\N{\rEng}I'll have the asperges sauce vinaigrette
Dialogue: 0,2:36:41.82,2:36:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,夏多布里昂牛排\N{\rEng}and then a Châteaubriand.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:43.37,2:36:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 炸薯条?　- 原味\N{\rEng}- Pommes frites? - Natures.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:45.58,2:36:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- 甜点呢?　- 等会儿再说\N{\rEng}- Comme dessert? - I'll decide later.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:48.71,2:36:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- 先生您呢?　- 一样\N{\rEng}- Monsieur? - I'll have the same.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:52.38,2:36:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,酒呢?\N{\rEng}For the wine?
Dialogue: 0,2:36:54.38,2:36:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你来决定吧,我要水就行\N{\rEng}You decide. I'll just have water.
Dialogue: 0,2:36:56.80,2:37:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你来选吧　- 谢谢\N{\rEng}- You decide. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:08.06,2:37:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你很老道\N{\rEng}You've been around.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:10.69,2:37:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,从哪儿学的这些法语菜名?谁教你那些东西的?\N{\rEng}Where'd you learn them parlez-vous français dishes?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:14.19,2:37:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,谁教你的?\N{\rEng}Who's teaching you that stuff?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:17.07,2:37:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,你是指逢场作戏的金主们吗?\N{\rEng}You mean a sugar daddy, who tries to teach me how to act?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:22.74,2:37:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我从书上学来的,我想学习一切知识\N{\rEng}I read books. I learn everything. I want to know everything.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:25.62,2:37:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,凡事都有计划不是很好吗?\N{\rEng}Doesn't it make sense to have plans?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:29.46,2:37:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,确实如此\N{\rEng}Yeah, it does.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:32.21,2:37:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,我呢?我在你的计划中吗?\N{\rEng}What about me? Am I in any of these plans?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:37.34,2:37:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,面条…\N{\rEng}Noodles...
Dialogue: 0,2:37:40.67,2:37:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,你是我曾经唯一…\N{\rEng}You're the only person that I have ever...
Dialogue: 0,2:37:44.39,2:37:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,唯一什么?\N{\rEng}Ever what? Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:48.97,2:37:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,什么?\N{\rEng}Ever what?
Dialogue: 0,2:37:51.56,2:37:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我唯一在乎的人\N{\rEng}That I ever cared about.
Dialogue: 0,2:37:54.48,2:37:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,但你是会把我锁在屋里,并把钥匙扔掉的人,对吧?\N{\rEng}But you'd lock me up and you throw away the key, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:02.66,2:38:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:05.28,2:38:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我想是这样吧\N{\rEng}Yeah, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:07.41,2:38:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,2:38:09.70,2:38:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,问题是我根本不在乎\N{\rEng}And the thing is, I probably wouldn't even mind.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:15.33,2:38:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- 所以?　- 所以我朝着我的目标努力\N{\rEng}- So? - So I got to get to where I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:20.34,2:38:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- 目标是哪里?　- 最高处\N{\rEng}- And where's that? - To the top.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:26.85,2:38:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在的语气和麦克希一样\N{\rEng}Now you sound just like Maxie.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:30.14,2:38:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你们俩太像了,难怪你们都不喜欢对方\N{\rEng}Youse both alike, that's why you hate each other so much.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:33.69,2:38:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,你想我离开吗?\N{\rEng}Do you want me to leave?
Dialogue: 0,2:38:40.94,2:38:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,不,我不想你离开\N{\rEng}No, I don't want you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:06.22,2:39:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,跳支舞吧?\N{\rEng}You dancing?
Dialogue: 0,2:39:08.97,2:39:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你在邀请我吗?　- 是的\N{\rEng}- You asking? - I'm asking.
Dialogue: 0,2:39:10.76,2:39:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,当然跳咯\N{\rEng}I'm dancing.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:25.67,2:40:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,为了避免发疯,你必须要把自己与外界隔绝\N{\rEng}And you had to keep yourself from going crazy, you had to cut yourself off from the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:30.51,2:40:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,不去想他\N{\rEng}Just not think about it.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:32.51,2:40:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,过去这么多年了,时间似乎…\N{\rEng}Yet there were years that went by, it seemed like...
Dialogue: 0,2:40:36.77,2:40:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,…停滞了,自己什么都没做\N{\rEng}...no time at all, because you're not doing anything.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:40.23,2:40:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有两件事我无法忘怀,一个是多明尼克\N{\rEng}There were two things I couldn't get out of my mind. One of them was Dominic.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:44.27,2:40:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,他死前说"我滑倒了"的样子\N{\rEng}The way he said, "I slipped," just before he died.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:48.78,2:40:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,还有就是你\N{\rEng}The other was you.
Dialogue: 0,2:40:57.25,2:41:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你曾经念《雅歌》给我听,还记得吗?\N{\rEng}How you used to read me your Song of Songs, remember?
Dialogue: 0,2:41:03.25,2:41:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,王女啊,你的脚在鞋中何其美好!\N{\rEng}How beautiful are your feet In sandals, O prince's daughter
Dialogue: 0,2:41:11.34,2:41:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我曾每晚读圣经\N{\rEng}I used to read the Bible every night.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:13.55,2:41:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,每晚都思念着你\N{\rEng}Every night I used to think about you.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:18.77,2:41:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你的肚脐如圆杯,不缺调和的酒\N{\rEng}Your navel is a bowl Well-rounded with no lack of wine
Dialogue: 0,2:41:23.94,2:41:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你的腰如一堆麦子,周围有百合花\N{\rEng}Your belly, a heap of wheat Surrounded with lilies
Dialogue: 0,2:41:27.69,2:41:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,你的两乳\N{\rEng}Your breasts
Dialogue: 0,2:41:31.66,2:41:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,如同其上的果子累累下垂\N{\rEng}Clusters of grapes
Dialogue: 0,2:41:34.83,2:41:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你鼻子的气味香如苹果\N{\rEng}Your breath, sweet-scented as apples
Dialogue: 0,2:41:46.75,2:41:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,没有人像我一样爱你\N{\rEng}Nobody's gonna love you the way I loved you.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:54.34,2:41:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,当我无法坚持下去的时候,我就会想起你\N{\rEng}There were times I couldn't stand it anymore, and I used to think about you.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:58.02,2:42:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我想,黛博拉还活着,她就在外面的某处\N{\rEng}I'd think, "Deborah lives. She's out there. She exists."
Dialogue: 0,2:42:02.27,2:42:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,对你的思念让我熬过了这一切\N{\rEng}And that would get me through it all.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:07.32,2:42:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道你对我有多重要吗?\N{\rEng}You know how important that was to me?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:16.12,2:42:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,面条,我明天就要动身,去好莱坞\N{\rEng}Noodles, I'm leaving tomorrow. I have to go to Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:18.91,2:42:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我今晚和你见面,就是要告诉你这件事\N{\rEng}I wanted to see you tonight to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:15.82,2:44:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:17.95,2:44:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,不要\N{\rEng}No!
Dialogue: 0,2:44:20.16,2:44:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不要,不\N{\rEng}No! No.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:26.58,2:44:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不,求你了…\N{\rEng}No. Please, no. No, please. No!
Dialogue: 0,2:44:31.84,2:44:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,不,求你了…\N{\rEng}No! No! No, please!
Dialogue: 0,2:44:37.30,2:44:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,不要,求求你,不…\N{\rEng}No, no! Please, no, no. No.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:45.77,2:44:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No!
Dialogue: 0,2:46:22.41,2:46:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,黛博拉\N{\rEng}Deborah.
Dialogue: 0,2:46:24.24,2:46:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,走开\N{\rEng}Get away! Get away!
Dialogue: 0,2:46:43.55,2:46:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我马上回来\N{\rEng}I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:17.25,2:47:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,送她回家\N{\rEng}Take her home.
Dialogue: 0,2:48:58.94,2:48:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:06.44,2:49:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:11.07,2:49:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你独自一人吗?　- 不,我还有你\N{\rEng}- You alone? - No, I'm with you, I hope.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:17.71,2:49:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,想跳舞吗?\N{\rEng}Wanna dance?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:20.17,2:49:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,不,我不想,你知道我想要的是什么吗?\N{\rEng}No, I'm not up to that. You know what I want?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:25.00,2:49:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我想上你\N{\rEng}I wanna get laid.
Dialogue: 0,2:49:29.17,2:49:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你想要的?\N{\rEng}That's what you're up to?
Dialogue: 0,2:49:43.44,2:49:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你每晚都喝成这样吗?还是唯独这次,在这个糟糕的晚上\N{\rEng}You get drunk like this every night, or this is just a bad night?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:00.04,2:50:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你是谁?洛克菲勒?　- 不是\N{\rEng}- Who are you, Mr. Rockefeller? - No.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:04.84,2:50:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- 怎么了?我给你了多少钱?　- 五十\N{\rEng}- Why, how much did I give you? - 50.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:08.17,2:50:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,五十?\N{\rEng}50?
Dialogue: 0,2:50:10.80,2:50:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你叫什么名字?　- 伊芙\N{\rEng}- What's your name? - Eve.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:21.69,2:50:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我想称呼你为黛博拉\N{\rEng}I'll call you Deborah.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:24.90,2:50:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,除此以外,我还能做些别的\N{\rEng}I did more complicated things for less.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:28.61,2:50:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 黛博拉,你爱我吗?　- 爱\N{\rEng}- Deborah... Do you love me? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:50:41.46,2:50:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是太美了\N{\rEng}You are so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,2:50:46.33,2:50:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,2:51:18.33,2:51:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你的脚在鞋中\N{\rEng}Your feet are so beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,2:51:21.33,2:51:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,何其美好\N{\rEng}Sandals...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:24.54,2:51:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,王女…\N{\rEng}Prince's daughter...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:28.59,2:51:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,黛博拉…\N{\rEng}Deborah...
Dialogue: 0,2:51:57.28,2:51:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,现在,我该干你了\N{\rEng}Now I'll fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,2:52:01.12,2:52:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,慢慢来\N{\rEng}Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,2:53:15.09,2:53:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,再见,谢咯,希望下次钱少点活多点吧.电912-5630黛博拉\N{\rEng}So long and thanks. Next time less money and more work, I hope. Tel. 912-5630 Deborah.
Dialogue: 0,2:55:35.14,2:55:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs18}中场休息
Dialogue: 0,2:57:05.55,2:57:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,看\N{\rEng}Well...
Dialogue: 0,2:57:07.76,2:57:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,谁回来了?\N{\rEng}look who's back.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:11.26,2:57:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么?\N{\rEng}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,2:57:16.52,2:57:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,御座\N{\rEng}It's a throne.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:20.44,2:57:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,曾是献给教皇的礼物\N{\rEng}It was a gift to a pope.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:23.69,2:57:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- 花了我八百块　- 这是十七世纪的宝物\N{\rEng}- Cost me 800 bucks. - It's from the 17th century.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:37.33,2:57:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你要这个做什么?\N{\rEng}So, what are you doing with it?
Dialogue: 0,2:57:42.63,2:57:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我正坐在上面\N{\rEng}I'm sitting on it.
Dialogue: 0,2:57:52.80,2:57:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- 有咖啡吗　- 有\N{\rEng}- You got any coffee around? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,2:58:07.82,2:58:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,谢了\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:27.40,2:59:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你度假的这段日子,我们拼命工作\N{\rEng}While you were on vacation, we were working overtime.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:39.33,2:59:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,工会付钱了\N{\rEng}The union paid off.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:44.33,2:59:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你的那一份\N{\rEng}That's your share.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:47.50,2:59:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,对,就连那个怪胎也有份,就是那个"两袖清风"的吉米\N{\rEng}Yeah. Even that geek. You know, Jimmy "Clean Hands."
Dialogue: 0,2:59:51.96,2:59:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,他尊敬我们,为了他们,我还受了点小伤\N{\rEng}He respects us. I shed a little blood for the cause.
Dialogue: 0,2:59:57.93,3:00:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,自己看,已经都见报了\N{\rEng}Here, it's all in the papers.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:00.51,3:00:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,电讯晨报,他们做了负面报道\N{\rEng}Morning Telegraph, they didn't like it.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:04.81,3:00:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说,"黑社会插手工会罢工,掀起血雨腥风"\N{\rEng}It says, "Underworld joins strikers in brutal battle."
Dialogue: 0,3:00:09.82,3:00:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,但邮报,则是正面报道\N{\rEng}But The Post, they liked it.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:13.78,3:00:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"即使是黑社会,也能带来好结局"\N{\rEng}"Ends justify means in decisive gangland encounter."
Dialogue: 0,3:00:17.91,3:00:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他们还批评了大西洋城的那一票事\N{\rEng}And they kvetched about the Atlantic City job.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:21.45,3:00:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,那些报社的人永远不知道自己要的是什么\N{\rEng}Newspaper guys never know what the fuck they want.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:31.92,3:00:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你们可以来找我啊　- 我们找过\N{\rEng}- Well, you could have looked for me. - We did.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:36.63,3:00:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,斜眼在中国佬那里找到了你\N{\rEng}Cockeye found you at the Chink's.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:39.26,3:00:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你早已吸得不省人事,根本认不出他\N{\rEng}So fucking doped up you didn't even recognize him.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:42.22,3:00:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,是的,你还猛叫我黛博拉\N{\rEng}There you were. You called me "Deborah."
Dialogue: 0,3:00:49.15,3:00:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,滚一边去,少管我的闲事\N{\rEng}Hey, go fuck yourself. Mind your own business.
Dialogue: 0,3:00:51.65,3:00:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我们他妈的向来同甘共苦,不受女人拖累\N{\rEng}We do our fucking business together, and fucking broads do not get in the way
Dialogue: 0,3:00:56.11,3:00:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你是知道的　- 是吗?\N{\rEng}- and you know it! - Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,3:00:57.57,3:00:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是啊　- 那她怎么会在这儿?\N{\rEng}- Yeah. - What's she doing here?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:01.28,3:01:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,今天又不是周六,她应该待在底特律接客才是\N{\rEng}Today ain't Saturday. She should be back in Detroit screwing like an assembly line.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:05.04,3:01:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,她现在只在这里接客了\N{\rEng}Well, she's screwing here now.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:08.00,3:01:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,而且只接待麦克希一位\N{\rEng}And only with Max.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:12.34,3:01:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,哦,是吗?\N{\rEng}Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:14.46,3:01:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- 她老公还在一旁偷窥吗?　- 不,我把他甩了\N{\rEng}- With her husband peeping through the keyhole? - No, I left him.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:23.10,3:01:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你一边和她同居,把她带到这来,一边让我别被女人拖累\N{\rEng}You live with her, you bring her here and you tell me not to mess with broads.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:27.02,3:01:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,- 可你忘了一件事　- 什么\N{\rEng}- You forget about one thing. - What's that?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:29.07,3:01:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我可不在乎她　- 麦克希\N{\rEng}- I don't give a fuck about her. - Max...
Dialogue: 0,3:01:31.27,3:01:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 闭嘴,闭嘴　- 麦克希,告诉我\N{\rEng}- Shut up! Shut up! - Maxie, tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,3:01:34.69,3:01:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,你打算上哪儿去度蜜月?妓院吗?\N{\rEng}What'll you spend your honeymoon on? Cathouse?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:36.69,3:01:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,- 麦克希　- 他妈的给我闭嘴\N{\rEng}- Maxie. - Shut the fuck up! Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:42.03,3:01:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,闭!嘴!\N{\rEng}Just shut up!
Dialogue: 0,3:01:48.58,3:01:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你要我甩了她?\N{\rEng}You want me to dump her?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:51.04,3:01:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你要我把她一脚踹开?\N{\rEng}You want me to kick her fucking ass out of here?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:55.05,3:01:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,是把她一脚踹开还是怎样?\N{\rEng}Want me to kick her ass out or what?
Dialogue: 0,3:01:57.55,3:02:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,你要我把…你给我滚!滚!\N{\rEng}You want me to kick... Get the fuck out! Get the fuck out! Get out!
Dialogue: 0,3:02:09.35,3:02:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,你以为我拿女人没辙吗?\N{\rEng}You gonna tell me I don't have a way with women?
Dialogue: 0,3:02:25.03,3:02:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 喂?　- 我是吉米,你是麦克希吗?\N{\rEng}- Hello. - This is Jimmy. Who's this, Max?
Dialogue: 0,3:02:27.95,3:02:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不,我是面条\N{\rEng}No, it's Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:32.08,3:02:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧,听着,我们今天需要你们\N{\rEng}Okay, listen. We're gonna need you guys today.
Dialogue: 0,3:02:36.25,3:02:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,我准备发表一个强硬的演讲,我想你们…\N{\rEng}I'm gonna be making a tough speech, and I think you...
Dialogue: 0,3:02:50.14,3:02:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,快,快\N{\rEng}Go, go!
Dialogue: 0,3:03:06.55,3:03:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs16}联邦俱乐部\N仅限会员
Dialogue: 0,3:03:13.46,3:03:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,发动汽车,我马上就来\N{\rEng}Start the engine. I'll be right with you.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:16.88,3:03:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,盖勒格先生希望你们知道,他对各位的帮助深表感谢\N{\rEng}Mr. Gallagher wants you to know how much he appreciates what you did.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:21.30,3:03:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,为此…\N{\rEng}To show his appreciation...
Dialogue: 0,3:03:34.14,3:03:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,这是给你们俩的信封\N{\rEng}Here's an envelope for the both of you.
Dialogue: 0,3:03:37.44,3:03:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,当需要收尾时,我会联系你的\N{\rEng}If we gotta complete the job, I'll let you know.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:19.52,3:04:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,被软木塞击中\N{\rEng}Wiped out by a blast of Cordon Rouge.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:22.15,3:04:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,现在康宁和他的老板们会怎么说呢?\N{\rEng}What would Crowning and his bosses say after that?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:25.99,3:04:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不怕你,结果呢?\N{\rEng}Never be afraid of you, then, would they?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:28.03,3:04:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,他们依旧不怕我,他们害怕的是你们\N{\rEng}They're still not afraid of me. It was you boys that scared them off.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:33.04,3:04:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你却不想要他们,算你幸运,有我这样一个党内领导人\N{\rEng}You didn't want these guys. You're lucky you got party leaders
Dialogue: 0,3:04:37.82,3:04:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,来关心工会\N{\rEng}like myself who care about the union.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:40.54,3:04:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,罢工已经结束,我们取得胜利,这才是重点,我说得没错吧,吉米?\N{\rEng}The strike is settled. We won. That's what counts. Am I right, Jim?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:44.55,3:04:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,可惜吉米无法亲自去签约,一定很难过吧?\N{\rEng}Yeah, it was tough for Jimmy not to be there to sign the contract though, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,3:04:48.51,3:04:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:51.72,3:04:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我难过的是\N{\rEng}What's tough is, you boys did more in one night
Dialogue: 0,3:04:54.81,3:04:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我两年的努力竟比不上你们一晚上的成就\N{\rEng}than I could in two years of talking.
Dialogue: 0,3:04:56.73,3:05:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- 不说这个了　- 敬美国工会最炙手可热的新人\N{\rEng}- Forget it. - To the hottest newcomer in American unions. - There you go.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:01.27,3:05:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- 吉米康威　- 这才像话\N{\rEng}- Jimmy Conway. - Now you're talking.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:03.53,3:05:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,干杯\N{\rEng}Roll out the barrel.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:05.11,3:05:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- 愿上天保佑　- 干了吧\N{\rEng}- And God bless. - Drink up. Suck it right down.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:09.57,3:05:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你们疯了?他马上要动手术了,还给他喝酒?\N{\rEng}You must be crazy giving him drinks. We're gonna operate in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:13.54,3:05:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,哎呀,急什么?\N{\rEng}Oh, what's the rush?
Dialogue: 0,3:05:15.58,3:05:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他们已经跟我说了,我注定要瘸脚一辈子了\N{\rEng}They already told me I'd be a gimp for the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:18.67,3:05:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,别担心吉米,少了一条腿,照样可以大步向前\N{\rEng}Don't worry, Jimmy. With one leg a little shy, you're gonna take giant steps.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:24.00,3:05:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,永远慢你一部,对吧,沙基?\N{\rEng}Yeah. And always one step right behind you, Sharkey?
Dialogue: 0,3:05:28.30,3:05:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,吉米,别让他们搞错脚了\N{\rEng}Make sure they work on the right leg, Jim.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:31.18,3:05:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,只是破了点皮而已嘛\N{\rEng}It's only blood, huh?
Dialogue: 0,3:05:41.35,3:05:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你们已经交到了一个真正的烈士朋友,要好好利用\N{\rEng}You boys got yourself a real martyr for a friend. Make it work for you.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:46.53,3:05:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,可是一个烈士还有什么可利用之处?\N{\rEng}Yeah, but what the hell are we gonna do with a martyr?
Dialogue: 0,3:05:50.07,3:05:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,时代不同了,禁酒令再维持不了多久了\N{\rEng}Times change. Prohibition ain't gonna last much longer.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:53.50,3:05:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,相信我,像你们这样的人到时大部分都得失业\N{\rEng}Take it from me, a lot of you guys is gonna be out of work.
Dialogue: 0,3:05:56.58,3:06:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,说下去,沙基先生,我们洗耳恭听\N{\rEng}Go on, Mr. Sharkey. We're interested.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:02.04,3:06:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,想过建立自己的事业吗?\N{\rEng}You ever think of setting yourselves up in business?
Dialogue: 0,3:06:05.96,3:06:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,那些运酒的卡车\N{\rEng}All those trucks they used to haul liquor,
Dialogue: 0,3:06:08.67,3:06:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,很快就会被贱卖\N{\rEng}soon be selling them for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:11.55,3:06:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的是一个全国性组织\N{\rEng}I'm talking about hundreds of vehicles controlled
Dialogue: 0,3:06:14.05,3:06:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,所控制的数百辆的卡车\N{\rEng}by a national organization.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:16.31,3:06:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,而他的背后是一个以吉米为首的强大的工会组织\N{\rEng}And supported by a powerful union headed by Jimmy Conway.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:20.06,3:06:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,不管你们提出什么要求,他都没有理由拒绝\N{\rEng}Whatever you ask, there's no way he can turn you down.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:24.82,3:06:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,沙基,你真是爱开玩笑\N{\rEng}You gotta be kidding, Sharkey.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:29.07,3:06:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"两袖清风"的吉米,会和我们做生意?\N{\rEng}Jimmy "Clean Hands" in business with us?
Dialogue: 0,3:06:33.03,3:06:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,他们洁身自好不了多久的,迟早会屈服\N{\rEng}They won't be clean for long, with the hands he's gonna shake.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:36.70,3:06:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是大好时机\N{\rEng}Everything in good time.
Dialogue: 0,3:06:54.18,3:06:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我们没兴趣　- 你是怎么了?\N{\rEng}- We're not interested. -What's the matter here, Noodles. You got a problem?
Dialogue: 0,3:06:58.35,3:07:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我们钱多得花不完,为什么不用来投资?这他妈能有什么问题?\N{\rEng}We got plenty of money tucked away. Why not invest it? What's the fucking problem?
Dialogue: 0,3:07:02.19,3:07:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我会说政党支持你们,而且我还有一些政界高层的朋友\N{\rEng}I'll put the party behind you. And I got friends in high places.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:08.03,3:07:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有兴趣,我也不相信政客之言\N{\rEng}I'm not interested in your friends in high places, and I don't trust politicians.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:11.82,3:07:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,你的想法还停留在街头混混的阶段\N{\rEng}You still think like some schmucks in the streets.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:14.20,3:07:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我们听了你的话,现在还只能抢抢醉汉的钱\N{\rEng}If we'd listened to you, we'd still be rolling drunks for a living.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:17.33,3:07:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你现在缺钱吗?　- 别惹我生气\N{\rEng}- You broke? - Don't bust my balls, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:19.83,3:07:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在谈论的可是真正的钱\N{\rEng}I am talking about real money.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:23.37,3:07:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是真正的钱,这里有很多,你需要吗?\N{\rEng}This is real money to me. It's a lot of money. You want any of it?
Dialogue: 0,3:07:29.51,3:07:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你街头气太重,一辈子也甩不掉　- 我喜欢这样,我感觉很好\N{\rEng}- You carry that stink of the street with the rest of your life. - I like the stink of the street. It makes me feel good.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:34.23,3:07:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这感觉,让我神清气爽\N{\rEng}I like the smell of it. It opens up my lungs.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:38.31,3:07:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,并且,让我觉得自己像个硬汉\N{\rEng}And it gives me a hard-on.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:40.56,3:07:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,麦克希,你累赘太多\N{\rEng}You're carrying dead weight around, Maxie.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:43.06,3:07:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,早晚有一天,你得它抛弃\N{\rEng}One of these days, you're gonna have to dump it.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:49.94,3:07:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,麦克希,你准备甩掉我的时候,记得跟我说一声\N{\rEng}Maxie, let me know when you're gonna dump me.
Dialogue: 0,3:07:52.90,3:07:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,对了,我要去趟佛罗里达,我想去海边走一走\N{\rEng}Meanwhile, I'll take a vacation in Florida. I got a yen for the seashore.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:19.47,3:08:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:23.06,3:08:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,听着,我考虑了一下\N{\rEng}Listen, I was thinking it over and...
Dialogue: 0,3:08:27.27,3:08:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我想…我自己也想去海边走一走\N{\rEng}I guess I kind of got a yen for the seashore myself.
Dialogue: 0,3:08:36.95,3:08:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,想去游泳吗?\N{\rEng}You wanna go swimming?
Dialogue: 0,3:08:39.41,3:08:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,是啊,咱们去游泳吧\N{\rEng}Yeah. Yeah, let's go for a swim.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:23.05,3:10:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,嘿,麦克希\N{\rEng}Hey, Maxie.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:25.60,3:10:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- 麦克希　- 嗯?\N{\rEng}- Max. - Huh?
Dialogue: 0,3:10:28.14,3:10:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我们存了多少钱?\N{\rEng}How much money we got put away?
Dialogue: 0,3:10:31.14,3:10:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么想起来问这个了?\N{\rEng}Why?
Dialogue: 0,3:10:35.40,3:10:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们失业了\N{\rEng}Because we're unemployed.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:47.23,3:10:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(禁酒令遭废除,十二月解除酒禁)
Dialogue: 0,3:10:52.88,3:10:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,大约一百万吧\N{\rEng}About a million bucks.
Dialogue: 0,3:10:55.88,3:11:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 是吗?你把钱放哪儿了?　- 我内裤里\N{\rEng}- Oh, yeah? Where'd you put it? - In my underwear.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:02.72,3:11:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- 要是这样,我早该找到了　- 别这样\N{\rEng}- I'd have found it there. - Hey.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:33.62,3:11:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们得重振旗鼓,麦克希,我有些不错的主意\N{\rEng}We gotta reorganize, Max. And I got a couple of good ideas.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:39.55,3:11:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,我也是\N{\rEng}Me too.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:41.55,3:11:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我有一百万,我就会安分些\N{\rEng}If I had a million bucks, I'd take it easy.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:44.76,3:11:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,等我们赚到两千万再说\N{\rEng}We'll take it easy when we got 20.
Dialogue: 0,3:11:48.51,3:11:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- 五千万　- 你要上哪儿弄去?\N{\rEng}- Fifty. - Where you gonna get that?
Dialogue: 0,3:11:55.19,3:11:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这里\N{\rEng}Right here.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:06.20,3:12:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么?\N{\rEng}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,3:12:11.37,3:12:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,梦想\N{\rEng}It's a dream.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:15.71,3:12:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我一生的梦想\N{\rEng}A dream I've been dreaming all my life.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:18.63,3:12:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我对天发誓,你我携手合作的话,我们一定能让梦想成真\N{\rEng}I swear to God, Noodles, you and me together, we can make it come true.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:26.68,3:12:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,什么梦想?\N{\rEng}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,3:12:33.18,3:12:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,联邦储备银行\N{\rEng}The Federal Reserve Bank.
Dialogue: 0,3:12:38.73,3:12:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们能做的最大的买卖\N{\rEng}It's the biggest step we can take, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:05.26,3:13:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你真是疯了\N{\rEng}You're really crazy.
Dialogue: 0,3:13:08.30,3:13:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不准你这么说,不准你再这么说我\N{\rEng}Don't you ever say that to me. Don't ever say that to me again!
Dialogue: 0,3:14:38.73,3:14:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,如此疯狂的事情能有多少把握成功?\N{\rEng}What chance is there that a crazy thing like this might succeed?
Dialogue: 0,3:14:44.82,3:14:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,别问我,问麦克希吧\N{\rEng}Don't ask me, ask Max.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:47.15,3:14:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你我都很清楚,这分明是自杀\N{\rEng}You know as well as I do that this is suicide,
Dialogue: 0,3:14:50.32,3:14:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,再明显不过了\N{\rEng}pure and simple, for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:53.74,3:14:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,没错,不过别跟我说,去跟他说,你们有自己的沟通方式\N{\rEng}Yeah, well, don't tell me, tell him. You got your own methods.
Dialogue: 0,3:14:59.66,3:15:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,我试了\N{\rEng}I tried.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:02.42,3:15:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他不再和我做爱了\N{\rEng}He doesn't want to screw anymore.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:08.46,3:15:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他现在满脑子想的都是这件事\N{\rEng}All he thinks about is this job.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:14.30,3:15:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,催泪瓦斯,人质,现在他正准备大干一票\N{\rEng}Tear gas, hostages, now he's gonna do this.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:17.56,3:15:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,不管你加入与否,他都做定了\N{\rEng}He's gonna do it with or without you.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:26.23,3:15:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,面条,我们从未喜欢过彼此\N{\rEng}Noodles, we've never liked each other.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:33.95,3:15:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,因为麦克希,我们彼此容忍.这次,我们何不一起\N{\rEng}We put up with each other for Max's sake. So why don't we just get together once
Dialogue: 0,3:15:39.75,3:15:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,为他做点什么\N{\rEng}and do something for him.
Dialogue: 0,3:15:52.22,3:15:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,之后\N{\rEng}And after that...
Dialogue: 0,3:15:55.22,3:15:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以做回敌人\N{\rEng}we can go back to being enemies.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:06.90,3:16:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道吗?如果你们先一步被关进监狱\N{\rEng}You know, if you were all in jail first,
Dialogue: 0,3:16:12.11,3:16:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,就不会再存在什么抢银行的机会了\N{\rEng}there wouldn't be any bank job.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:26.75,3:16:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,这想法是从你朋友麦克希那儿学来的\N{\rEng}I got the idea from your friend Max.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:31.25,3:16:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,什么意思?\N{\rEng}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,3:16:35.55,3:16:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,他嘲笑你,揶揄你\N{\rEng}He laughs at you. He makes fun of you.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:40.72,3:16:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,他说你拿伊芙一点办法都没有\N{\rEng}He says Eve has got you by the balls.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:44.18,3:16:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,每次经过这里,你都会吓得屁滚尿流\N{\rEng}Every time you walk past this place, you shit in your pants.
Dialogue: 0,3:16:48.27,3:16:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你会想尽办法让条子把你抓了\N{\rEng}You'd do anything for the cops to pick you up
Dialogue: 0,3:16:50.65,3:16:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,如此一来你就不必参与此事了,真的吗?\N{\rEng}so you wouldn't have to do this job. Is that true, huh?
Dialogue: 0,3:17:07.04,3:17:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,那就这么做啊!\N{\rEng}Well, then do it.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:08.79,3:17:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,把他弄进监狱吧,不需要太久\N{\rEng}Do it. Put him in jail. Put him in jail. Not long.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:12.25,3:17:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,足够他打消这个念头就好\N{\rEng}Just long enough so he can get the idea out of his mind.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:17.93,3:17:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不舍得离开他,那就把你自己也送进监狱吧\N{\rEng}If you can't stand being away from him, put yourself there too.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:24.64,3:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,好死不如赖活\N{\rEng}Better off than being dead.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:31.98,3:17:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道该怎么做\N{\rEng}You know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:37.91,3:17:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不愿意的话,就让我来好了\N{\rEng}And if you don't, I will.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:44.16,3:17:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,下车\N{\rEng}Get out!
Dialogue: 0,3:17:45.58,3:17:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,坐出租车去吧,我还忙着呢,下车\N{\rEng}Take a cab. I'm busy. I got things to do. Get out.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:55.38,3:17:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,面条\N{\rEng}Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:17:57.55,3:18:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,尽快做决定,好吗?\N{\rEng}Make up your mind fast, huh?
Dialogue: 0,3:19:25.18,3:19:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,怎么了?\N{\rEng}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,3:19:27.77,3:19:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,玩得不开心吗?\N{\rEng}Aren't you having a good time?
Dialogue: 0,3:19:37.07,3:19:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,为何今晚还要出去?\N{\rEng}Why are you going out tonight?
Dialogue: 0,3:19:40.19,3:19:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,禁酒令就快解除了\N{\rEng}Why bother now that prohibition is almost over?
Dialogue: 0,3:19:45.49,3:19:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,大家都在卖酒,我们有些朋友也正在急着脱手\N{\rEng}Everybody's selling. We got some friends who have a lot of booze they wanna get rid of.
Dialogue: 0,3:19:49.58,3:19:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,价格很低,所以我们准备接手\N{\rEng}Practically nothing. So we figured, why not.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:00.21,3:20:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我会离开一段时间\N{\rEng}I'm gonna be gone for a while.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:03.30,3:20:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我在酒店等你\N{\rEng}I'll be waiting at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:07.05,3:20:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我喜欢你深夜回来,唤醒我\N{\rEng}I like it when you come home late and wake me up.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:16.77,3:20:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我今晚不回家\N{\rEng}I'm not gonna be home tonight.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:25.99,3:20:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我明晚也不能回家\N{\rEng}I'm not gonna be home tomorrow either.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:28.99,3:20:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你只是出去几个小时\N{\rEng}I thought these things only take a couple of hours.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:39.34,3:20:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,女士们,先生们,我要为肥摩酒吧的终结而喝一杯\N{\rEng}Ladies and gents, I drink to the demise of Fat Moe's speakeasy.
Dialogue: 0,3:20:45.55,3:20:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,我是说,谁还愿意躲在这儿喝合法的酒啊\N{\rEng}I mean, who the hell wants to drink here legally anyway, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,3:20:50.35,3:20:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,来吧,摩,倒酒吧\N{\rEng}Okay. Come on, Moe, set them up. Go on, get in there.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:08.87,3:21:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你眼里有东西\N{\rEng}Here's mud in your eye.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:17.79,3:21:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,两位\N{\rEng}Boys.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:22.67,3:21:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,为我们最后的一批货干杯吧\N{\rEng}Let's drink to our last shipment.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:24.97,3:21:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚我们喝下的不只是酒\N{\rEng}There's more onboard tonight than just booze.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:27.97,3:21:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,还有我们十年的岁月,十年,不虚此行\N{\rEng}It's 10 years of our lives. Ten years that were really worth living.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:33.56,3:21:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,说得对\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:53.41,3:21:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,面条\N{\rEng}Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:56.62,3:21:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,面条\N{\rEng}Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:21:59.92,3:22:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 干杯　- 干杯\N{\rEng}- L'Chaim. - L'Chaim.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:05.51,3:22:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我得等多久?\N{\rEng}How long will I have to wait?
Dialogue: 0,3:22:11.76,3:22:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,一年半左右吧\N{\rEng}A year and a half, more or less.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:16.64,3:22:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,表现好的话,六个月\N{\rEng}Six months off for good behavior.
Dialogue: 0,3:22:19.27,3:22:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你要做什么?　- 不要问\N{\rEng}- What are you gonna do? - Don't ask.
Dialogue: 0,3:23:56.87,3:23:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,接线生\N{\rEng}Operator.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:00.04,3:24:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,请接警察局\N{\rEng}Police, please.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:07.21,3:24:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,第五分局,哈洛伦警长\N{\rEng}Fifth Precinct. Sergeant Halloran.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:12.22,3:24:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rEng}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:14.72,3:24:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,谁?需要帮助吗?\N{\rEng}Who's speaking? Can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,3:24:17.97,3:24:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在吗?　- 在\N{\rEng}- Hello. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:22.56,3:24:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我有线报给你\N{\rEng}I got a good tip for you.
Dialogue: 0,3:24:50.80,3:24:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谁?　- 麦克希,开门\N{\rEng}- Yeah, who is it? - It's Max. Open the door.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:00.47,3:25:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你怎么了?不舒服吗?　- 不,我很好\N{\rEng}- What's the matter with you? You sick? -No, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:04.69,3:25:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,你气色可不怎么样\N{\rEng}You don't look it.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:08.48,3:25:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,你今晚还是待在家里比较好吧?\N{\rEng}Maybe you'd better stay home tonight, huh?
Dialogue: 0,3:25:11.82,3:25:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么\N{\rEng}- Why? - Huh.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:17.20,3:25:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你自己清楚,我已经观察你一晚上了\N{\rEng}You know, I've been watching you all night.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:21.62,3:25:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你整晚都在喝酒\N{\rEng}And you've been drinking like a fish.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:25.33,3:25:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,在给自己壮胆吗?\N{\rEng}Trying to get your courage up?
Dialogue: 0,3:25:31.25,3:25:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只不过是进一船酒\N{\rEng}We're only bringing in a shipment of booze.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:36.09,3:25:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,就把你吓成这样了?\N{\rEng}It's got so you're even scared to do that.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:41.05,3:25:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,或许你还是回家待着比较好\N{\rEng}Maybe you just better stay home tonight.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:44.85,3:25:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,和伊芙在一起\N{\rEng}With Eve.
Dialogue: 0,3:25:56.74,3:26:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,麦克希,记住,我会与你共进退\N{\rEng}Hey, Maxie, everywhere you go, I go too. Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:11.00,3:26:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,也许沙基说得对\N{\rEng}Maybe Sharkey was right.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:13.63,3:26:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,或许我应该甩掉你\N{\rEng}Maybe I ought to just dump you.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:25.56,3:26:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你真的是疯了　- 不许你这么说\N{\rEng}- You're really crazy. - Never say that.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:29.69,3:26:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,不!许!\N{\rEng}Don't say it!
Dialogue: 0,3:26:39.74,3:26:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,麦克希耍了我们,面条,他一心求死\N{\rEng}Max made fools of us, Noodles. He wanted to die.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:43.99,3:26:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道他父亲死于疯人院吗?\N{\rEng}Did you know his old man died in the nut house?
Dialogue: 0,3:26:47.20,3:26:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,麦克希不想落得同样的下场\N{\rEng}Max didn't want to end up the same way.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:50.25,3:26:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他设了个局,设计让我们向警察告密\N{\rEng}So he put the idea in our heads to tip off the cops.
Dialogue: 0,3:26:54.55,3:26:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,当他们停下车时,麦克希就率先开枪\N{\rEng}And when they stopped the truck, Max started shooting first
Dialogue: 0,3:26:59.59,3:27:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,好让自己中弹\N{\rEng}just to get himself killed.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:20.07,3:27:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这是什么?\N{\rEng}What is this?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:25.45,3:27:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,开幕夜\N{\rEng}Opening night.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:28.29,3:27:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,十五年前\N{\rEng}Fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:31.42,3:27:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,那是谁?\N{\rEng}Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:35.13,3:27:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,基金会创始人\N{\rEng}Patron saint of the place.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:39.51,3:27:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,还有个女演员\N{\rEng}And some actress.
Dialogue: 0,3:27:42.55,3:27:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识她吗?\N{\rEng}Do you know her?
Dialogue: 0,3:27:45.93,3:27:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:09.16,3:28:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,(以下引自莎士比亚戏剧"安东尼与克莉奥佩特拉",朱生豪译本)
Dialogue: 0,3:28:16.17,3:28:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,我不应该这样卑劣地留恋着人间\N{\rEng}This proves me base:
Dialogue: 0,3:28:19.63,3:28:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,要是她先遇见了鬈发的安东尼,他一定会向她问起我\N{\rEng}If she first meet the curled Antony, he'll make demand of her,
Dialogue: 0,3:28:22.59,3:28:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,她将要得到他的第一个吻,夺去我天堂中无上的快乐\N{\rEng}and spend that kiss which is my heaven to have.
Dialogue: 0,3:28:49.16,3:28:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,来,你杀人的毒物\N{\rEng}Come, thou mortal wretch,
Dialogue: 0,3:28:54.16,3:28:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,用你的利齿咬断这一个生命的葛藤吧\N{\rEng}with thy sharp teeth this knot intrinsicate of life at once untie:
Dialogue: 0,3:29:01.51,3:29:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,可怜的蠢东西\N{\rEng}poor venomous fool.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:06.05,3:29:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,张开你的怒口,赶快完成你的使命\N{\rEng}Be angry, and dispatch.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:11.89,3:29:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,啊!但愿你能够说话\N{\rEng}Oh, couldst thou speak,
Dialogue: 0,3:29:15.64,3:29:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,让我听你称那伟大的凯撒为一头无谋的驴子\N{\rEng}that I might hear thee call great Caesar ass unpolicied!
Dialogue: 0,3:29:20.02,3:29:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- 东方的明星啊! - 静,静!\N{\rEng}- Oh eastern star! - Peace, peace!
Dialogue: 0,3:29:22.90,3:29:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有见我的婴孩在我的胸前吮吸乳汁\N{\rEng}Dost thou not see my baby at my breast,
Dialogue: 0,3:29:25.36,3:29:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- 使我安然睡去吗? - 啊,我的心碎了!啊,我的心碎了!\N{\rEng}- that sucks the nurse asleep? - Oh, break! Oh, break!
Dialogue: 0,3:29:29.03,3:29:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,像香膏一样甜蜜\N{\rEng}As sweet as balm,
Dialogue: 0,3:29:31.83,3:29:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,像微风一样温柔\N{\rEng}as soft as air, as gentle...
Dialogue: 0,3:29:37.42,3:29:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,——啊,安东尼\N{\rEng}Oh, Antony!
Dialogue: 0,3:29:47.55,3:29:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,——让我把你也拿起来\N{\rEng}Nay, I will take thee too.
Dialogue: 0,3:29:57.48,3:29:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我还有什么留恋呢——\N{\rEng}What should I stay...
Dialogue: 0,3:29:59.86,3:30:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在这万恶的世间?再会吧!\N{\rEng}In this vile world? So, fare thee well.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:04.32,3:30:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,现在,死神,你可以夸耀了,一个绝世的佳人已经为你所占有\N{\rEng}Now boast thee, death, in thy possession lies a lass unparallel'd.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:09.32,3:30:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,软绵绵的窗户啊,关上了吧\N{\rEng}Downy windows, close,
Dialogue: 0,3:30:11.53,3:30:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,闪耀着金光的福玻斯再也看不见这样一双华贵的眼睛\N{\rEng}and golden Phoebus never be beheld of eyes again so royal!
Dialogue: 0,3:30:16.04,3:30:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,你的王冠歪了,让我替你戴正,然后我也可以玩去了\N{\rEng}Your crown's awry. I'll mend it, and then play.
Dialogue: 0,3:30:57.08,3:30:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你好,黛博拉\N{\rEng}Hello, Deborah.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:06.96,3:31:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,不想说几句吗?\N{\rEng}Aren't you gonna say anything?
Dialogue: 0,3:31:16.39,3:31:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,自那之后,还有什么好说的\N{\rEng}What is someone supposed to say after...
Dialogue: 0,3:31:20.35,3:31:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,三十多年了\N{\rEng}...more than 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:28.53,3:31:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧,比如"你好吗?你气色不错"或者\N{\rEng}Well, how about, "How you doing? You're looking good." Or...
Dialogue: 0,3:31:36.49,3:31:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"我本希望我再也不会见到你"\N{\rEng}"I was hoping I'd never see you again."
Dialogue: 0,3:31:42.08,3:31:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我真没想到会有这么一天\N{\rEng}I never thought I would.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:46.17,3:31:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,有一点不同\N{\rEng}There's a difference.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:49.21,3:31:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,至少你还认得我\N{\rEng}At least you recognized me, that's something.
Dialogue: 0,3:31:51.68,3:31:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,女演员的记性特别好\N{\rEng}Actresses have good memories.
Dialogue: 0,3:32:05.27,3:32:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,想喝点什么吗?\N{\rEng}You want a drink?
Dialogue: 0,3:32:11.82,3:32:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,那我自己喝了\N{\rEng}I'm having one.
Dialogue: 0,3:32:24.67,3:32:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,玛戈\N{\rEng}Margo.
Dialogue: 0,3:32:27.46,3:32:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- 小姐,什么事?　- 没事了,你可以走了\N{\rEng}- Yes, miss? - That's all for now. You can go.
Dialogue: 0,3:32:30.34,3:32:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,是的,小姐\N{\rEng}All right, miss.
Dialogue: 0,3:32:37.43,3:32:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,她称呼你"小姐"\N{\rEng}She called you "miss."
Dialogue: 0,3:32:40.64,3:32:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,你一直未婚?\N{\rEng}You never got married?
Dialogue: 0,3:32:43.89,3:32:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,没有\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:32:49.11,3:32:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你独居吗?\N{\rEng}You live alone?
Dialogue: 0,3:32:58.78,3:33:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:07.13,3:33:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,你去哪儿了?\N{\rEng}Where were you?
Dialogue: 0,3:33:12.38,3:33:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,外地\N{\rEng}I was out of town.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:17.64,3:33:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,回来很久了吗?\N{\rEng}Have you been back long?
Dialogue: 0,3:33:21.39,3:33:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,有几天时间了\N{\rEng}A couple of days.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:23.98,3:33:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,要留下来吗?\N{\rEng}Are you staying?
Dialogue: 0,3:33:37.87,3:33:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,看情况\N{\rEng}That depends.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:42.20,3:33:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,你为何想来看我\N{\rEng}Why do you want to see me?
Dialogue: 0,3:33:46.12,3:33:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,两个原因\N{\rEng}Two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:48.63,3:33:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,其一,我想知道你为了当演员,离我而去\N{\rEng}First, I wanted to see if you did the right thing,
Dialogue: 0,3:33:51.88,3:33:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这决定是否正确\N{\rEng}turning me down to become an actress.
Dialogue: 0,3:33:58.30,3:33:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,结果呢?\N{\rEng}Well?
Dialogue: 0,3:34:02.56,3:34:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你做到了,你成功了\N{\rEng}You did. You're terrific.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:20.57,3:34:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,"青春不能永相伴"\N{\rEng}"Age cannot wither her."
Dialogue: 0,3:34:23.87,3:34:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,这部剧好像是为你量身定做的\N{\rEng}It's like the play was written for you.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:30.33,3:34:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,另一个原因呢?\N{\rEng}What was the other reason?
Dialogue: 0,3:34:33.00,3:34:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,另一个原因\N{\rEng}The other reason...
Dialogue: 0,3:34:38.51,3:34:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,是决定是否出席明晚的一场宴会\N{\rEng}...is to decide whether I should go to a party tomorrow night.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:49.56,3:34:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,宴会?\N{\rEng}Party?
Dialogue: 0,3:34:54.40,3:34:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,是的,在长岛\N{\rEng}Yeah, on Long Island.
Dialogue: 0,3:34:58.40,3:35:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,秘书长贝利\N{\rEng}A Secretary Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:05.41,3:35:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,你认识秘书长贝利吗?\N{\rEng}Do you know Secretary Bailey?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:09.42,3:35:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,不认识\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:13.04,3:35:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但我还是收到了请帖\N{\rEng}But I was invited anyway.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:23.89,3:35:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你们不认识,他又为何要邀请你?\N{\rEng}If you don't know each other, why were you invited?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:26.93,3:35:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:30.10,3:35:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我以为你或许知道答案\N{\rEng}I thought you might know why.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:33.19,3:35:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我?\N{\rEng}Me?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:34.77,3:35:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么是我?\N{\rEng}Why me?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:41.82,3:35:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你认识他\N{\rEng}Because you know him.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:45.20,3:35:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- 谁?　- 大卫\N{\rEng}- Who is it? - It's me. David.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:46.83,3:35:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- 别,大卫　- 我能进来吗?\N{\rEng}- No, David. - Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,3:35:49.71,3:35:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,别,你在外面等下,我会叫你的\N{\rEng}No. Just wait outside, David. I'll call you.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:52.75,3:35:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,好,我就在门外\N{\rEng}Okay, I'll be right here.
Dialogue: 0,3:35:57.92,3:36:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- 贝利想见我是为了什么?　- 你来这儿是为了问我这个?\N{\rEng}- What does Secretary Bailey want from me? - You came here to ask me that?
Dialogue: 0,3:36:01.93,3:36:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- 他为什么要发请帖给我?　- 我不知道\N{\rEng}- Why'd he send me an invitation? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:05.10,3:36:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你的请帖我怎么会知道?我什么都不知道\N{\rEng}Why should I know about your invitations? I don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:09.64,3:36:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你来这儿的目的何在?我什么都不知道\N{\rEng}What do you want from me? Why did you come here? I know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:13.81,3:36:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在的演技很差\N{\rEng}Now you're a lousy actress.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:19.32,3:36:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,秘书长贝利是谁?\N{\rEng}Who is Secretary Bailey?
Dialogue: 0,3:36:30.91,3:36:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,秘书长贝利是个富商\N{\rEng}Secretary Bailey is a rich businessman.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:40.26,3:36:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,他以移民的身份来到美国,然后赚了很多钱\N{\rEng}He came to the United States as an immigrant and made a lot of money...
Dialogue: 0,3:36:45.05,3:36:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,在旧金山,洛杉矶,他在那一带待了三十年\N{\rEng}...in San Francisco and L.A., where he's lived for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,3:36:49.18,3:36:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,这些我都知道,报纸上有报道,你还知道什么?\N{\rEng}I know all that. It's all in the papers. What else is there?
Dialogue: 0,3:36:59.69,3:37:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,他娶了一个富家千金\N{\rEng}He married a very wealthy woman.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:03.99,3:37:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,有一个孩子\N{\rEng}They had a child.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:06.70,3:37:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,她死于难产\N{\rEng}She died when the child was born.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:10.33,3:37:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,几年前,他进入政坛,移居这里\N{\rEng}A few years ago, he went into politics. Moved here.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:15.04,3:37:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都过去了,我不是在说这些,我想知道的是现在\N{\rEng}That's all past history. I'm not talking about that. I'm talking about now.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:20.25,3:37:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,现在他遇到麻烦了\N{\rEng}Right now he's in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:24.55,3:37:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,你不如就直截了当告诉我,你是他的情人\N{\rEng}Why don't you just tell me you've been living with him all these years,
Dialogue: 0,3:37:28.10,3:37:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,多年来一直在和他同居\N{\rEng}and you're his lover.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:38.90,3:37:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,岁月催人老啊,面条\N{\rEng}Age can wither me, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:45.61,3:37:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都老了\N{\rEng}We're both getting old.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:53.58,3:37:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,回忆是我们仅存的东西了\N{\rEng}All that we have left now are our memories.
Dialogue: 0,3:37:59.79,3:38:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你去参加周六的宴会,那么我们仅存的回忆也将消散\N{\rEng}If you go to that party on Saturday night, you won't have those anymore.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:07.13,3:38:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,把请帖撕了吧\N{\rEng}Tear up that invitation.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:11.97,3:38:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这边有个出口\N{\rEng}There's an exit back this way.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:15.52,3:38:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,面条,从那边走吧\N{\rEng}Noodles, go through it.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:21.11,3:38:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,一直走\N{\rEng}Keep walking.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:23.19,3:38:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,不要回头\N{\rEng}Don't turn around.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:26.78,3:38:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,求你了,面条\N{\rEng}Please, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:29.11,3:38:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我求你了\N{\rEng}I'm begging you. Please.
Dialogue: 0,3:38:38.58,3:38:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,你怕我一回头就会变成"盐柱"吗?\N{\rEng}Are you afraid that I'll turn into a pillar of salt?
Dialogue: 0,3:38:45.63,3:38:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你从这扇门出去的话,是的\N{\rEng}If you go out that door, yes.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:47.61,3:39:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,这是秘书长贝利的儿子\N{\rEng}This is Secretary Bailey's son.
Dialogue: 0,3:39:50.78,3:39:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他的名字叫大卫,就像你的名字\N{\rEng}His name's David, just like yours.
Dialogue: 0,3:42:26.73,3:42:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我必须承认,宴会真是个绝妙的主意,秘书长先生\N{\rEng}I must admit this party was a wonderful idea, Mr. Secretary.
Dialogue: 0,3:42:32.40,3:42:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这就好像是在说,"虽然距离听证会只有五天时间\N{\rEng}It's a bit like saying, "I'm going up before the Commettee in 5 days,
Dialogue: 0,3:42:36.11,3:42:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但我问心无愧\N{\rEng}like, my conscience is clear.
Dialogue: 0,3:42:38.74,3:42:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,全纽约的达官贵人都是我的座上客\N{\rEng}The most important people in New York are my guests.
Dialogue: 0,3:42:42.87,3:42:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这将是一个难忘的夜晚"\N{\rEng}It's going to be a night to remember."
Dialogue: 0,3:42:46.16,3:42:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,特别是房子引爆的瞬间\N{\rEng}Especially if the house blows up.
Dialogue: 0,3:42:49.21,3:42:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,你把另一个炸弹藏哪了?\N{\rEng}Where are you putting the next bomb?
Dialogue: 0,3:42:52.84,3:42:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,冰箱?\N{\rEng}In the freezer?
Dialogue: 0,3:42:55.59,3:42:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,还是洗手间?\N{\rEng}Or in the toilet?
Dialogue: 0,3:43:05.60,3:43:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经丧失理智了\N{\rEng}You can't even think straight anymore.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:09.69,3:43:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我这么说吧\N{\rEng}I'll tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:12.06,3:43:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,已经有一群人等着在你葬礼上献花\N{\rEng}There's a waiting list of people would like to send flowers to your funeral.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:18.99,3:43:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- 如果你想的话,我现在就能随便说上十个人的名字 - 没错\N{\rEng}- I can point out ten right now, if you like me to. -Yes.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:22.78,3:43:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们任何人都不会比你,还有你的工会\N{\rEng}But none of them wants to read my obituary in front of the Committee as much as you do.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:28.08,3:43:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,更想在听证会上宣读我的讣告吧\N{\rEng}You and your union.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:33.34,3:43:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只是想扭转局势\N{\rEng}We just want to resolve this situation clean.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:36.25,3:43:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这话我他妈已经听了三十五年了!\N{\rEng}I've heard that same song from you for 35 fucking years!
Dialogue: 0,3:43:39.97,3:43:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,你清楚你是在和谁说话吗?\N{\rEng}Who do you think you are talking to?
Dialogue: 0,3:43:44.01,3:43:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我,是我帮你,还有那些寄生虫们建立了基金会\N{\rEng}I helped you to make a fortune, you and the rest of those parasites!
Dialogue: 0,3:43:47.81,3:43:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,那不过是劳工和管理层达成的妥协之间\N{\rEng}It was a reasonable arrangement between labour and management.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:53.81,3:43:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,百分之二给了他们,而百分之四十给了你\N{\rEng}2% for them and 40% for you.
Dialogue: 0,3:43:57.65,3:44:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,你这辈子只做了两件事\N{\rEng}You defend them and you screw them. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,3:44:01.41,3:44:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,先保护了他们而后又抛弃了他们\N{\rEng}It's been the story of your life.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:04.62,3:44:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- 你以为还会有人相信你吗?　- 有\N{\rEng}- Do you think anybody believe you anymore? -Some.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:08.91,3:44:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,但不会再有人相信你了\N{\rEng}But no one believes in you anymore,
Dialogue: 0,3:44:11.58,3:44:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你犯了错,而我没有\N{\rEng}because you have made mistakes and I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:16.00,3:44:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不过这已经不是重点了\N{\rEng}But that's beside the point.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:20.51,3:44:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,现在的当务之急是\N{\rEng}The important thing right now is that
Dialogue: 0,3:44:23.47,3:44:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,你我一起纠正错误\N{\rEng}you and I straighten out these transfers of authority.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:29.18,3:44:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,如我们之前说好的那样\N{\rEng}Now it's all as we have agreed.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:34.81,3:44:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经让律师拟好了文件\N{\rEng}I have had our lawyers drawn it up.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:39.40,3:44:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,你只要签个字就可以了\N{\rEng}All you have to do is sign.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:50.00,3:44:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我的遗嘱?\N{\rEng}My last will?
Dialogue: 0,3:44:53.54,3:44:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,如此处境下,你已经没得选了\N{\rEng}You are not in a position to exercise your will.
Dialogue: 0,3:44:58.92,3:45:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,我放弃了一切\N{\rEng}I give up everything.
Dialogue: 0,3:45:03.01,3:45:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,百分之十二的财产会留给你的孩子\N{\rEng}12% would be set aside for your boy.
Dialogue: 0,3:45:05.93,3:45:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,那些钱足够他过一辈子了\N{\rEng}In that way he can be assured of living to a ripe old age.
Dialogue: 0,3:45:11.35,3:45:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我不签的话,是不是他就什么都没有了?\N{\rEng}Or not, if I don't sign?
Dialogue: 0,3:46:24.80,3:46:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你为什么不自己留着?\N{\rEng}Why don't you take care of this by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,3:46:29.05,3:46:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,希望在今晚嘈杂的晚会上\N{\rEng}I'd be very happy for you tonight, if during all the noise of the party
Dialogue: 0,3:46:32.60,3:46:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 我能听到一声枪响　- 或许能如你所愿\N{\rEng}- I heard a shot. - Maybe you will.
Dialogue: 0,3:47:48.34,3:47:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,请进\N{\rEng}Please go in.
Dialogue: 0,3:48:04.23,3:48:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你在等什么?\N{\rEng}What are you waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,3:48:10.24,3:48:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白,贝利先生\N{\rEng}I don't understand, Mr. Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,3:48:39.39,3:48:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,坐吧,面条\N{\rEng}Sit down, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:48:45.73,3:48:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,别拘束\N{\rEng}Make yourself comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:05.92,3:49:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴你接受了我的邀请\N{\rEng}I'm glad you accepted my invitation.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:08.80,3:49:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我只是好奇\N{\rEng}Well, I was curious.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:13.76,3:49:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,如此之多的达官贵人聚在这里\N{\rEng}So many important people in one place.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:17.10,3:49:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,通常来说大难临头各自飞\N{\rEng}Yes. Well, the rats usually desert a sinking ship.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:21.43,3:49:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,但这回,他们貌似没有弃我而不顾\N{\rEng}But in my case, they appear to be flocking onboard.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:36.99,3:49:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,是的从报纸上得知了你的处境\N{\rEng}Yeah, well, I read about your troubles in the newspapers.
Dialogue: 0,3:49:42.20,3:49:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但凡像你这样位高权重之人\N{\rEng}But a man in your position, with all your power and all your privileges...
Dialogue: 0,3:49:47.08,3:49:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,总得承担些责任\N{\rEng}...has to assume a certain amount of responsibility...
Dialogue: 0,3:49:52.01,3:49:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,以及一些风险\N{\rEng}...a certain amount of risk.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:01.93,3:50:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你为何请我来这儿,贝利先生\N{\rEng}Why'd you ask me to come here, Mr. Bailey?
Dialogue: 0,3:50:08.02,3:50:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,请帖根本不代表什么,你是清楚的\N{\rEng}That invitation doesn't mean a goddamn thing, and you know it.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:12.90,3:50:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,重要的是箱里的东西\N{\rEng}All that counts is what was in that suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:18.12,3:50:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,钱,还有合约\N{\rEng}The money and the contract.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:23.66,3:50:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不过上面没说是谁的合约\N{\rEng}It didn't say who the contract was on, though.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:28.21,3:50:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你还不明白吗?\N{\rEng}Haven't you figured that out yet?
Dialogue: 0,3:50:32.34,3:50:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你,贝利先生?\N{\rEng}You, Mr. Bailey?
Dialogue: 0,3:50:47.69,3:50:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经不拿枪很多很多年了\N{\rEng}I haven't had a gun in my hand for many, many years.
Dialogue: 0,3:50:53.03,3:50:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,我现在老眼昏花,戴上眼镜也是一样,我的手会颤抖\N{\rEng}My eyes aren't too good, even with my glasses. My hands shake.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:01.45,3:51:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- 而且我也不想射偏　- 别扯你的鬼话了\N{\rEng}- And I wouldn't want to miss, Mr. Bailey. - Cut the bullshit, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:07.00,3:51:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我早已是一个死人\N{\rEng}I'm already a dead man.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:10.67,3:51:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,请最后给我个机会,好让我偿还我欠你的债\N{\rEng}At least give me the chance to settle the debt that I owe to you.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:15.76,3:51:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,要不是因为调查委员会\N{\rEng}I'll never make it before the investigating committee.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:19.43,3:51:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,他们现在都怕我把他们全拖下水\N{\rEng}They're scared to death I'll implicate the whole bunch of 'em.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:23.76,3:51:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他们肯定会除掉我\N{\rEng}They gotta get rid of me.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:28.64,3:51:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,择日不如撞日\N{\rEng}Today is as good a day as any.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:33.94,3:51:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你来吧,面条\N{\rEng}You do it, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:37.11,3:51:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我只愿死在你的手下\N{\rEng}You're the only person I can accept it from.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:47.37,3:51:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你看,我找到你的住处\N{\rEng}You see, I found out where you were.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:50.12,3:51:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,把你请来这里\N{\rEng}I brought you back here for this.
Dialogue: 0,3:51:54.55,3:51:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,了结我们的恩怨\N{\rEng}To even the score between you and me.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:00.13,3:52:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以从那里出去\N{\rEng}You can get out through there.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:09.85,3:52:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那儿径直通向马路,不会有人察觉\N{\rEng}It leads right down to the street. Nobody will see you.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:21.15,3:52:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我不明白你在说什么,贝利先生,你什么都不亏欠我\N{\rEng}I don't know what you're talking about, Mr. Bailey. You don't owe me a thing.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:33.50,3:52:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,你的眼泪模糊了你的视线,躺在街上那烧焦的尸体并不是我\N{\rEng}Your eyes were too full of tears to see that it wasn't me lying there, burned up on that street.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:40.47,3:52:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,死者另有其人\N{\rEng}It was somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:43.93,3:52:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,你惊吓过度,没有察觉到警察也参与了其中\N{\rEng}You were too shocked to realize that the cops were in on it too.
Dialogue: 0,3:52:49.48,3:52:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,那是一场瞒天过海的大骗局,面条\N{\rEng}That was a syndicate operation, Noodles.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:02.99,3:53:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,你疯了\N{\rEng}You're crazy.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:07.45,3:53:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,很久以前,你也跟我说过同样的话\N{\rEng}You said that to me once before, a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:12.00,3:53:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,可当时,我神智清醒得很\N{\rEng}My mind was never as clear as it was at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:16.21,3:53:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我毁了你的一生\N{\rEng}I took away your whole life from you.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:19.92,3:53:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我住你的房子\N{\rEng}I've been living in your place.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:24.01,3:53:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我抢走了一切\N{\rEng}I took everything.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:28.01,3:53:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我拿走了你的钱\N{\rEng}I took your money.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:30.89,3:53:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我夺走了你的女人\N{\rEng}I took your girl.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:33.73,3:53:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,留给你的只是三十五年的悔恨,因你误以为你害死了我\N{\rEng}All I left for you was 35 years of grief over having killed me.
Dialogue: 0,3:53:40.36,3:53:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,你为何还不开枪?\N{\rEng}Now, why don't you shoot?
Dialogue: 0,3:55:16.79,3:55:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你说得没错,我杀过人\N{\rEng}It's true, I have killed people, Mr. Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:19.92,3:55:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,有时是为了自卫,有时是为了钱\N{\rEng}Sometimes to defend myself. Sometimes for money.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:24.96,3:55:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,曾有许多人来找我们\N{\rEng}And many people used to come to us.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:27.72,3:55:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,商业伙伴,对手\N{\rEng}Business partners, rivals...
Dialogue: 0,3:55:31.01,3:55:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,爱人\N{\rEng}...lovers.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:33.56,3:55:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我们接受了一部分工作,而拒绝了另一部分\N{\rEng}Some of the jobs we took, and some we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:51.07,3:55:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,而像这回的工作,就是我们永远都不会去碰的\N{\rEng}Yours is one we would never touch, Mr. Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,3:55:54.91,3:55:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你想用这种方式报复我?\N{\rEng}Is this your way of getting revenge?
Dialogue: 0,3:56:01.83,3:56:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,不是\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,3:56:06.76,3:56:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我对人生的看法\N{\rEng}It's just the way I see things.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:12.57,3:57:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是十点二十五分\N{\rEng}It's 10:25...
Dialogue: 0,3:57:16.66,3:57:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我已经输得一无所有\N{\rEng}...and I've got nothing left to lose.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:21.96,3:57:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,当有朋友背叛你时,你就该反击\N{\rEng}When you've been betrayed by a friend, you hit back.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:30.96,3:57:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,动手吧\N{\rEng}Do it.
Dialogue: 0,3:57:54.95,3:57:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,秘书长\N{\rEng}You see, Mr. Secretary...
Dialogue: 0,3:57:59.58,3:58:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,我也有一个故事\N{\rEng}...I have a story also.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:02.62,3:58:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不过比你的更简单些\N{\rEng}A little simpler than yours.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:06.29,3:58:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,许多年前,我有一个朋友,挚友\N{\rEng}Many years ago I had a friend, a dear friend.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:12.63,3:58:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我为了救他而把他送进了监狱\N{\rEng}I turned him in to save his life...
Dialogue: 0,3:58:16.09,3:58:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,但他却被杀害\N{\rEng}...but he was killed.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:19.68,3:58:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,但那正是他想要的\N{\rEng}But he wanted it that way.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:23.56,3:58:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我们情同手足\N{\rEng}It was a great friendship.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:28.86,3:58:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我们都落得一个凄惨的结局\N{\rEng}It went bad for him, and it went bad for me too.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:37.87,3:58:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,晚安,贝利先生\N{\rEng}Good night, Mr. Bailey.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:49.21,3:58:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我希望他们的调查一无所获\N{\rEng}I hope the investigation turns out to be nothing.
Dialogue: 0,3:58:54.84,3:58:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,眼见一生的努力化为乌有,令人心痛\N{\rEng}It'd be a shame to see a lifetime of work go to waste.
